ools, globally recognized and respected within the industry.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Earn 35 PDUs with 35 hours of Instructor-Led Training</li>\n</ul>' WHERE value_id=26280;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Delve into the dynamic world of DevOps with our Google Professional Cloud DevOps Engineer Certification Prep course. Designed for IT professionals and DevOps enthusiasts, this course offers a deep dive into the practices and tools essential for building and maintaining reliable and efficient systems on the Google Cloud Platform (GCP). The curriculum encompasses core DevOps principles, including continuous integration (CI), continuous delivery (CD), and site reliability engineering (SRE). You will gain hands-on experience in managing cloud-based infrastructure and services, mastering the use of GCP for automating the deployment, scaling, and monitoring of cloud solutions.</p>\n<p>This course is an ideal pathway for those aspiring to become certified Google Cloud DevOps Engineers. Our expert instructors will guide you through the intricacies of implementing DevOps processes in a cloud environment, focusing on optimizing resource utilization and improving operational efficiency. The training includes practical exercises and real-world case studies, ensuring you not only prepare for the certification exam but also acquire skills that are directly applicable in your professional role. Whether you''re aiming to enhance your current skills or transition into a DevOps role, this course will equip you with the knowledge and confidence to excel in the fast-evolving domain of cloud computing. Join us to elevate your career and become a leader in implementing DevOps best practices on Google Cloud</p>\n\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n<h2>Register for Google Cloud Certification</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://cloud.google.com/learn/certification?hl=en" title="Google Cloud Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>' WHERE value_id=26462;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive into the world of advanced network engineering with our comprehensive course on ''CCNP Enterprise: Implementing Cisco Enterprise Advanced Routing and Services (300-410 ENARSI)''. This course is meticulously designed to equip you with in-depth knowledge and practical skills required to excel in the 300-410 ENARSI exam. You will explore key areas such as Layer 3 technologies, VPN services, infrastructure security, and services, ensuring a complete understanding of Cisco''s advanced routing and network troubleshooting.</p>\n<p>Our expert instructors, equipped with real-world experience, will guide you through the complexities of enterprise network solutions. The curriculum emphasizes hands-on training, preparing you for real-world challenges while aligning with Cisco''s exam objectives. Whether you''re aiming to advance your career in network engineering or seeking to validate your skills with the CCNP Enterprise certification, this course is your gateway to success in the dynamic field of advanced networking.</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong>&nbsp;- Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Certification</strong>&nbsp;-&nbsp;The participant will be able to attempt the 300-310 Implementing Cisco Enterprise Advance Routing and Services (ENARSI) certification exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the&nbsp;300-310&nbsp;Implementing Cisco Enterprise Advance Routing and Services (ENARSI) accreditation from CISCO. This certification validates a participant''s proficiency in configuring, operating, and troubleshooting medium-sized networks.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/credentials/certifications/exams/pl-200/" title="Exam PL-200: Microsoft Power Platform Functional Consultant" target="_blank">here</a></span>. We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center.&nbsp;Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n<p>For WSQ funding, please checkout the details at&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/wsq-cisco-certified-network-professional-ccnp-for-enarsi-training.html" title="WSQ - Cisco Certified Network Professional (CCNP) for ENARSI Training">WSQ - Cisco Certified Network Professional (CCNP) for ENARSI Training</a></span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=27791;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive into the world of Neo4j and get a comprehensive understanding of its fundamentals. From basic graph theory and graph structures to Cypher fundamentals, our course covers every essential aspect. Learn how Neo4j implements index-free-adjacency and understand the intricacies of reading and writing data to Neo4j. Embrace the power of graph data modeling, understanding nodes, relationships, and the significance of graph data models.</p>\n<p>Expand your knowledge with intermediate topics like Neo4j Database Administration and data importing techniques. Grasp the nuances of Neo4j Graph Data Science, discover the synergy between Neo4j and Python, and prepare effectively for the Neo4j Certified Professional Exam. Enrich your skillset and become a proficient user of Neo4j with Tertiary Courses.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n<h2>Certification Exam</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://graphacademy.neo4j.com/courses/neo4j-certification/" title="Neo4j Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n\n<p>For WSQ funding, please checkout the details at&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/wsq-neo4j-professional-graph-database-course.html" title="WSQ - Neo4j Professional Graph Database Course">WSQ - Neo4j Professional Graph Database Course</a></span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>\n\n</div>' WHERE value_id=34063;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive into the world of Neo4j and get a comprehensive understanding of its fundamentals. From basic graph theory and graph structures to Cypher fundamentals, our course covers every essential aspect. Learn how Neo4j implements index-free-adjacency and understand the intricacies of reading and writing data to Neo4j. Embrace the power of graph data modeling, understanding nodes, relationships, and the significance of graph data models.</p>\n<p>Expand your knowledge with intermediate topics like Neo4j Database Administration and data importing techniques. Grasp the nuances of Neo4j Graph Data Science, discover the synergy between Neo4j and Python, and prepare effectively for the Neo4j Certified Professional Exam. Enrich your skillset and become a proficient user of Neo4j with Tertiary Courses.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<p><iframe frameborder="0" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/jCzQPr-BBhk?rel=0&amp;controls=0&amp;showinfo=0" width="400"></iframe></p>\n\n<h2>Certification Exam</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://graphacademy.neo4j.com/courses/neo4j-certification/" title="Neo4j Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>' WHERE value_id=35087;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on your game development journey with our Basic Unity Game Development Training. This course offers a solid introduction to Unity, the world''s leading game engine, and C# programming, equipping you with the skills to create 2D and 3D games from scratch. You will explore Unity&rsquo;s interface, install essential tools, and learn to manipulate GameObjects within your projects. The course emphasizes hands-on learning, ensuring you gain practical experience in coding C# scripts, understanding variables, and controlling object behaviors within Unity.</p>\n<p>Take your learning further by prototyping your first 3D game. This stage introduces essential Unity features such as the Transform component, Rigidbody physics, and collision detection. You&rsquo;ll master advanced concepts like loops, coroutines, and the GetComponent function to manipulate and control GameObjects. By the end of the course, you&rsquo;ll have the knowledge and skills to create interactive 3D prototypes, preparing you for more advanced game development projects or a career as a junior Unity developer.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p class="p1">No funding is available for this course.</p>\n<p>For WSQ funding, please checkout the details at&nbsp;<a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/wsq-c-programming-methodologies-for-unity-game-development.html"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">WSQ - Mastering Game Development with Unity and C# Programming Basics</span></a></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=39200;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on your game development journey with our Basic Unity Game Development Training. This course offers a solid introduction to Unity, the world''s leading game engine, and C# programming, equipping you with the skills to create 2D and 3D games from scratch. You will explore Unity&rsquo;s interface, install essential tools, and learn to manipulate GameObjects within your projects. The course emphasizes hands-on learning, ensuring you gain practical experience in coding C# scripts, understanding variables, and controlling object behaviors within Unity.</p>\n<p>Take your learning further by prototyping your first 3D game. This stage introduces essential Unity features such as the Transform component, Rigidbody physics, and collision detection. You&rsquo;ll master advanced concepts like loops, coroutines, and the GetComponent function to manipulate and control GameObjects. By the end of the course, you&rsquo;ll have the knowledge and skills to create interactive 3D prototypes, preparing you for more advanced game development projects or a career as a junior Unity developer.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n' WHERE value_id=39353;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Blockchain is essentially a decentralised and distributed database peer-to-peer technology (Web3) that was popularised by the Bitcoin global cryptocurrency platform since 2009. There has been a lot of hype around Blockchain and Web3 technology in recent times. Almost all Fin-Tech heavy weights are pouring investments into various Blockchain projects such as DeFi, GameFi, Metaverse, NFT etc .Governments and regulators are also equally interested in this disruptive technology.</p>\n\n<p>The potential applications for Blockchains and Bitcoin-like cryptocurrencies are enormous.&nbsp;This course will teach you the fundamentals on Crypto,, NFT, Metaverse, DeFi, GameFi. It also covers the Crypto Security and how you can protect your Crypto from hacking and fraud.</p>\n\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=43681;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Step into the next level of accounting proficiency with our Advanced QuickBooks Online Plus Training. Designed for those aiming for mastery, this course delves deep into the complexities of budgeting, streamlining payroll processes, and managing projects seamlessly within QuickBooks. Get insights into bank reconciliation and learn the intricacies of handling fixed assets and their depreciation.</p>\n<p>The course doesn&rsquo;t just stop at traditional features. Embrace the modern era of accounting by exploring the full potential of QuickBooks Mobile Apps, ensuring you can manage your finances on-the-go. Whether you''re an experienced accountant or an entrepreneur seeking to expand your financial expertise, this training promises a thorough understanding and hands-on practice. Join Tertiary Courses to unlock superior accounting capabilities.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n\n<p>This course has no funding.</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=43990;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a transformative journey with our Robotic Process Automation course, centered around the power and flexibility of UIPath. This course lays the foundation by offering hands-on experience in UIPath operations, ensuring you grasp the core concepts and techniques integral to automating business processes.</p>\n<p>Dive deeper into the world of automation by mastering control flow scripting, an essential component to enhance the efficiency and accuracy of robotic tasks. With a balanced mix of theoretical knowledge and practical application, this course aims to equip learners with the skills necessary to navigate the rapidly evolving landscape of Robotic Process Automation.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p class="p1">No funding is available for this course.</p>\n<p>For WSQ funding, please checkout the details at&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/wsq-rpa-course.html" title="WSQ Robotics Process Automation (RPA) for Beginners">WSQ - Robotics Process Automation (RPA) for Beginners</a></span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>\n</div>\n' WHERE value_id=44025;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive into the revolutionary world of Robotic Process Automation with our Basic Robotic Process Automation course using UIPath. This course is designed for individuals aiming to harness the power of automation, providing foundational knowledge on UIPath operations &ndash; a leading tool in the RPA industry.</p>\n<p>Delve deeper into the course highlights that focus on UIPath Operations, offering a comprehensive understanding of control flow scripting. By the end of this course, participants will be equipped with practical skills, laying a solid foundation for advanced automation projects and tasks.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n' WHERE value_id=44162;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Step into the next level of accounting proficiency with our Advanced QuickBooks Online Plus Training. Designed for those aiming for mastery, this course delves deep into the complexities of budgeting, streamlining payroll processes, and managing projects seamlessly within QuickBooks. Get insights into bank reconciliation and learn the intricacies of handling fixed assets and their depreciation.</p>\n<p>The course doesn&rsquo;t just stop at traditional features. Embrace the modern era of accounting by exploring the full potential of QuickBooks Mobile Apps, ensuring you can manage your finances on-the-go. Whether you''re an experienced accountant or an entrepreneur seeking to expand your financial expertise, this training promises a thorough understanding and hands-on practice. Join Tertiary Courses to unlock superior accounting capabilities.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n' WHERE value_id=44207;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>The Apply Scrum Methodology in Agile Environment course is designed to help professionals effectively implement Scrum principles in Agile projects. Participants will explore the fundamentals of Scrum, including Agile foundations, Scrum frameworks, and key roles such as the Scrum Master, Product Owner, and Development Team. The course emphasizes establishing team norms, managing shared resources, and creating collaborative team spaces to ensure smooth project execution.</p>\n<p>The course also dives deep into Agile and Scrum project management, covering Scrum events such as sprint planning, daily scrums, backlog refinement, sprint reviews, and retrospectives. Learners will gain expertise in tracking and reporting progress using burn-down and burn-up charts. Additionally, participants will explore Scrum artifacts like product backlogs, backlog ordering, product increments, and the definition of done, ensuring they can deliver high-quality outcomes in Agile environments.</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong>&nbsp;- Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Ceritification</strong>&nbsp;-&nbsp;The participant will be able to attempt the Professional Scrum Master exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the Professional Scrum Master Training&nbsp;accreditation. This certification validates their project management skills, knowledge, and experience. The PMP certification in Singapore enhances career prospects by demonstrating proficiency in project management processes and tools, globally recognized and respected within the industry.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>' WHERE value_id=44245;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on the journey to becoming a Google Associate Cloud Engineer with our comprehensive certification prep course. Gain an in-depth understanding of core cloud services, their application, and how to manage Google Cloud Platform technology efficiently. This course is designed to equip you with the knowledge and skills to design, develop, manage, and administer application infrastructure and data solutions on Google Cloud.</p>\n<p>Delve into the essential elements of GCP, including IAM, networking, auto-scaling, and load balancing to ensure you''re prepared for the exam and beyond. Our expert-led training will help you understand how to set up a cloud solution environment, plan and configure a cloud solution, as well as deploy and implement a cloud solution, ensuring a complete grasp of the platform''s capabilities. With this course, you''ll be well on your way to attaining your Google Associate Cloud Engineer certification, advancing your career, and embracing the cloud computing revolution.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Set up and test Google Cloud solutions in accordance to security standards</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Detect and resolve Google Cloud integration issues related to AWS services.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Conduct implementation tests and escalate unresolved Google Cloud issues</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1O30IBwOYwg_hrEg2Z4y8peceEB7s8ZXO/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Google Associate Cloud Engineer Training (Synchronous e-Learning) Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Google Associate Cloud Engineer Training (Synchronous e-Learning) Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Cloud Computing ICT-DIT-3020-1.1&nbsp;</strong>under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Register for Google Cloud Certification</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://cloud.google.com/learn/certification?hl=en" title="Google Cloud Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;We are&nbsp; Kryterion Authorized Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$1,600.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$144.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$944.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$624.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2023041024" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023041024" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=44991;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>The WSQ Fast-Track to Unreal Game Development for Aspiring Game Developers course provides an intensive introduction to Unreal Engine, equipping participants with the essential tools and skills for game development. Learners will explore Unreal Editor, master level design, and learn to interpret technical briefs to create level maps and import gameplay assets seamlessly. The course introduces Blueprint visual scripting to design game mechanics, implement scenarios, and build interactive gameplay elements like progress bars, state machines, and dynamic buttons.</p>\n<p>Participants will also gain expertise in testing, debugging, and maintaining documentation for game development. Hands-on projects include creating animations, enemy AI, minimaps, scoring systems, and interactive features like sliding doors and day-night cycles. By the end of the course, learners will be prepared to develop, script, and document their own game levels while ensuring smooth functionality through robust testing processes.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Interpret technical briefs to implement level maps and import gameplay assets using Unreal game engines.</li>\n<li>LO2: Apply Unreal Blueprint for game development and design.</li>\n<li>LO3: Test and debug Unreal scripts while maintaining up-to-date documentation for level scripting.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Yss-99EUjESA5LgxPMKn3AwBG8GUd0BR/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Fast-Track to Unreal Game Development for Aspiring Game Developers Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Fast-Track to Unreal Game Development for Aspiring Game Developers Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><span lang="EN-GB">Game Level Development</span>&nbsp;<span lang="EN-GB">MED-GDP-2009-1.1&nbsp;</span><span></span>&nbsp;</strong>under Media Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$900</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$81.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$531.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$351.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2025052674" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2025052674" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2025052674" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2025052674) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=45249;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Step into the realm of cutting-edge Business Intelligence with our QlikView Business Intelligence Training course. QlikView, a leading BI tool, empowers businesses to transform raw data into actionable insights, and this training offers a holistic approach to mastering its vast capabilities.</p>\n<p>Starting with the essentials of creating dynamic data visualizations, you''ll progress to loading data effectively and building captivating interactive dashboards that offer real-time insights. Dive deeper into the heart of QlikView with intricate scripting, data modeling techniques, and learn to craft precise expressions to meet business requirements. Further enhance your BI skills with set analysis, ensuring data interpretation is both thorough and precise. Concluding with an understanding of QlikView''s robust security protocols, you''ll leave with the confidence and knowledge to utilize QlikView in driving data-led business decisions.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p class="p1">No funding is available for this course.</p>\n</div>\n' WHERE value_id=45897;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Step into the realm of cutting-edge Business Intelligence with our QlikView Business Analytics Training course. QlikView, a leading BI tool, empowers businesses to transform raw data into actionable insights, and this training offers a holistic approach to mastering its vast capabilities.</p>\n<p>Starting with the essentials of creating dynamic data visualizations, you''ll progress to loading data effectively and building captivating interactive dashboards that offer real-time insights. Dive deeper into the heart of QlikView with intricate scripting, data modeling techniques, and learn to craft precise expressions to meet business requirements. Further enhance your BI skills with set analysis, ensuring data interpretation is both thorough and precise. Concluding with an understanding of QlikView''s robust security protocols, you''ll leave with the confidence and knowledge to utilize QlikView in driving data-led business decisions.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n' WHERE value_id=45986;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive deep into the world of cloud architecture with our Google Professional Cloud Architect Certification Exam Prep course. This meticulously crafted course is designed to provide you with the essential knowledge and skills required to excel in the Google Professional Cloud Architect Certification Exam. Our expert instructors will guide you through the complexities of the Google Cloud Platform, ensuring you are well-prepared to tackle the challenges of the exam and achieve certification success.</p>\n<p>Our course covers a comprehensive range of topics, providing you with a thorough understanding of cloud architecture and the Google Cloud Platform. You will gain practical insights and hands-on experience, enhancing your cloud skills and opening up new career opportunities. Enroll now and take the first step towards becoming a certified Google Professional Cloud Architect and elevating your career to new heights</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n<h2>Register for Google Cloud Certification</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://cloud.google.com/learn/certification?hl=en" title="Google Cloud Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;We are&nbsp; Kryterion Authorized Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=46136;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive deep into the world of cloud architecture with our Google Professional Cloud Architect Certification Exam Prep course. This meticulously crafted course is designed to provide you with the essential knowledge and skills required to excel in the Google Professional Cloud Architect Certification Exam. Our expert instructors will guide you through the complexities of the Google Cloud Platform, ensuring you are well-prepared to tackle the challenges of the exam and achieve certification success.</p>\n<p>Our course covers a comprehensive range of topics, providing you with a thorough understanding of cloud architecture and the Google Cloud Platform. You will gain practical insights and hands-on experience, enhancing your cloud skills and opening up new career opportunities. Enroll now and take the first step towards becoming a certified Google Professional Cloud Architect and elevating your career to new heights</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Register for Google Cloud Certification</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://cloud.google.com/learn/certification?hl=en" title="Google Cloud Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>' WHERE value_id=46195;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>The ISC2 Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP) Exam Prep course is meticulously designed for professionals seeking to deepen their knowledge and skills in information security. The course begins with a focus on Security and Risk Management, emphasizing professional ethics, security concepts, the legal environment, and secure design principles. Participants will gain a clear understanding of the key aspects of Asset Security, including managing information assets and data security life cycles.</p>\n<p>Moving into the intricacies of Security Architecture and Engineering, the course covers vulnerabilities assessment, cryptographic systems, and the essentials of cryptanalysis. Communication and Network Security is another critical topic, providing insight into the OSI and TCP/IP models and their application in secure network design. Identity and Access Management (IAM) is thoroughly explored, highlighting the importance of managing identities, access controls, and authentication systems.</p>\n<p>Additionally, the course emphasizes Security Assessment and Testing, enabling learners to design effective security assessment strategies and analyze organizational security performance. Security Operations is a key module that includes incident management, logging, and monitoring activities, as well as implementing backup and recovery strategies. The final topic, Software Development Security, delves into the vulnerabilities inherent in software systems, malware and ransomware threats, and the implementation of security controls in software development ecosystems. This course ensures that participants are well-prepared for the CISSP exam, equipping them with the knowledge to develop action plans, evaluate technologies, introduce security controls, and address lapses in organizational security standards.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Assess application and infrastructure component adherence to security standards, integrating organizational security operational procedures.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Develop specific action plans for business units, incorporating corporate security policies, standards, and guidelines.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Evaluate technologies and tools for addressing security gaps, aligning with security policy considerations.</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Introduce security controls in alignment with corporate security policies and frameworks.</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Implement security guidelines and protocols, ensuring compliance and understanding of data security controls and compliance requirements</li>\n<li>LO6:&nbsp;Review and confirm the adequacy of information security controls, focusing on types of security controls and implementation procedures.</li>\n<li>LO7:&nbsp;Highlight areas for improvement in security and propose revisions to security guidelines, incorporating techniques for process assessment against security standards.</li>\n<li>LO8:&nbsp;Identify and address lapses in organizational security standards, focusing on issues threatening information security and integrity.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1eMVZ2R_U3e221GV0_fKda8COKFVu3TCm/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - ISC2 Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP)Training Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - ISC2 Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP) Training Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of<strong>&nbsp;Security Governance ICT-SNA-4020-1.1&nbsp;</strong>under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have&nbsp;achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://home.pearsonvue.com/Clients/CompTIA.aspx" title="CompTia Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>. We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center.</p>\n<h2>Exam Voucher</h2>\n<p>This course include a Autodesk Exam Voucher at Our Pearson Vue Test Center.</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$3,500.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$315.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$2,065.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$1,365.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2024043392" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2024043392" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year.&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></span></span></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2024043392" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2024043392) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=49161;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Immerse yourself in the field of Sustainability Reporting with a focus on GRI (Global Reporting Initiative) standards through our comprehensive course. Gain the essential knowledge and skills needed to produce high-quality sustainability reports adhering to globally recognized standards. Understand how to assess, measure, and effectively communicate your organization''s impact on critical sustainability issues such as climate change, human rights, governance, and social well-being.</p>\n<p>Our course provides a deep dive into the GRI standards, equipping you with the know-how to contribute to your company''s sustainability agenda and increase its corporate responsibility profile. This knowledge will empower you to drive sustainable development within your organization, paving the way for enhanced business performance and a better future for all. Align your business goals with the larger objective of sustainability and make a lasting impact on your organization and society at large</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>For WSQ funding, please checkout the details at&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/wsq-sustainability-reporting-and-gri-standards.html" title="WSQ - Sustainability Reporting and GRI Standards">WSQ - Sustainability Reporting and GRI Standards</a></span></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=49472;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Immerse yourself in the field of Sustainability Reporting with a focus on GRI (Global Reporting Initiative) standards through our comprehensive course. Gain the essential knowledge and skills needed to produce high-quality sustainability reports adhering to globally recognized standards. Understand how to assess, measure, and effectively communicate your organization''s impact on critical sustainability issues such as climate change, human rights, governance, and social well-being.</p>\n<p>Our course provides a deep dive into the GRI standards, equipping you with the know-how to contribute to your company''s sustainability agenda and increase its corporate responsibility profile. This knowledge will empower you to drive sustainable development within your organization, paving the way for enhanced business performance and a better future for all. Align your business goals with the larger objective of sustainability and make a lasting impact on your organization and society at large</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n' WHERE value_id=49558;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a transformative journey with the Qlik Sense Business Analytics Training at Tertiary Courses. Qlik Sense, a front-runner in the business analytics sphere, offers a dynamic platform for data-driven decision-making. This course has been meticulously designed to ensure participants grasp the nuances of the tool, enabling them to extract actionable insights from their data.</p>\n<p>Commencing with an in-depth look at the Qlik Sense Interface, trainees will be adeptly guided on connecting to diverse data sources, ensuring a robust foundation. From there, the course delves into the intricacies of data modelling, preparation, and creating compelling visualizations. By mastering Qlik Sense expressions and the potent set analysis feature, participants will be equipped to transform raw data into visual stories, making strategic decisions with precision. Join us and harness the power of Qlik Sense for superior business analytics.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=52644;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a transformative journey with the Qlik Sense Business Analytics Training at Tertiary Courses. Qlik Sense, a front-runner in the business analytics sphere, offers a dynamic platform for data-driven decision-making. This course has been meticulously designed to ensure participants grasp the nuances of the tool, enabling them to extract actionable insights from their data.</p>\n<p>Commencing with an in-depth look at the Qlik Sense Interface, trainees will be adeptly guided on connecting to diverse data sources, ensuring a robust foundation. From there, the course delves into the intricacies of data modelling, preparation, and creating compelling visualizations. By mastering Qlik Sense expressions and the potent set analysis feature, participants will be equipped to transform raw data into visual stories, making strategic decisions with precision. Join us and harness the power of Qlik Sense for superior business analytics.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n' WHERE value_id=52806;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a journey to mastery with our Advanced RPA Training focused on UIPath. This course, curated for professionals and enthusiasts alike, delves into intricate aspects of RPA including data scraping, orchestrator operations, and more, ensuring a comprehensive grasp on the subject.</p>\n<p>Our curriculum accentuates on the key highlights: from efficient data scraping and recording methods to the seamless integration of UIPath Orchestrator. Further, participants will understand the nuances of error handling and the fascinating realm of cognitive activities. By the conclusion, attendees will possess a robust set of skills, poised to lead in the evolving landscape of Robotic Process Automation.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p class="p1">No funding is available for this course.</p>\n<p>For WSQ funding, please checkout the details at&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/wsq-rpa-course.html" title="WSQ - Robotics Process Automation (RPA) for Beginners">WSQ - Robotics Process Automation (RPA) for Beginners</a></span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=53062;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive deep into the world of C# programming within Unity software with our Unity Certified User Programmer Exam Prep. This course is meticulously designed to cover the essentials of creating interactivity in games, apps, and other immersive experiences. You will learn the ins and outs of Unity software and C# programming, ensuring you are well-prepared to take on the certification exam.</p>\n<p>With the exam objectives aligned with the current industry standards set by professionals and educators, our course guarantees that you receive the most relevant and up-to-date knowledge. We understand the importance of hands-on experience, and that''s why we recommend individuals to have at least 150 hours of Unity software use and training before obtaining this certification. Our course is not just about passing the exam; it''s about empowering you with the skills and knowledge needed to excel in your career. So, gear up and get ready to unlock new opportunities with our Unity Certified User Programmer Exam Prep.</p>\n<h2>Pearson Vue Test Center</h2>\n<p>We are authorised Pearson Vue Test Center. You can book the Unity User Certification exam at our premise.&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://home.pearsonvue.com/unity/" title="Unity Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>. We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n</div>\n' WHERE value_id=53185;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive deep into the world of C# programming within Unity software with our Unity Certified User Programmer Exam Prep. This course is meticulously designed to cover the essentials of creating interactivity in games, apps, and other immersive experiences. You will learn the ins and outs of Unity software and C# programming, ensuring you are well-prepared to take on the certification exam.</p>\n<p>With the exam objectives aligned with the current industry standards set by professionals and educators, our course guarantees that you receive the most relevant and up-to-date knowledge. We understand the importance of hands-on experience, and that''s why we recommend individuals to have at least 150 hours of Unity software use and training before obtaining this certification. Our course is not just about passing the exam; it''s about empowering you with the skills and knowledge needed to excel in your career. So, gear up and get ready to unlock new opportunities with our Unity Certified User Programmer Exam Prep.</p>\n\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://home.pearsonvue.com/unity/" title="Unity Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>. We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n' WHERE value_id=53557;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a journey to mastery with our Advanced RPA Training focused on UIPath. This course, curated for professionals and enthusiasts alike, delves into intricate aspects of RPA including data scraping, orchestrator operations, and more, ensuring a comprehensive grasp on the subject.</p>\n<p>Our curriculum accentuates on the key highlights: from efficient data scraping and recording methods to the seamless integration of UIPath Orchestrator. Further, participants will understand the nuances of error handling and the fascinating realm of cognitive activities. By the conclusion, attendees will possess a robust set of skills, poised to lead in the evolving landscape of Robotic Process Automation.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n' WHERE value_id=53609;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Uncover the potential of application integration and automation with our WSQ-endorsed course on Power Apps and Power Automate. The course covers the essentials of building customized apps without coding and creating automated workflows that can transform manual processes into streamlined operations. Through hands-on exercises and real-world scenarios, you''ll acquire actionable skills that can significantly enhance business efficiency.</p>\n<p>By the end of this course, you''ll be adept at leveraging Power Apps and Power Automate for practical business solutions. You''ll know how to build apps tailored to specific business needs and automate repetitive tasks, freeing up valuable time and resources. Whether you''re an IT professional, a business analyst, or a manager aiming to optimize business processes, this course will equip you with the skills you need to drive business transformation.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul></ul>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Identify opportunities to use Power Platform app</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Utilize and test Power Automate flows for business automation</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Create Power apps and verify their functionalities</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Improve Power apps with Power Automate flows.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/17GbkxQiOvvw7IVw-woPajDWs909ePu7c/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Applications Integration with Power Apps and Power Automate" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Applications Integration with Power Apps and Power Automate Course Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of <strong>Applications Integration</strong>&nbsp;<strong><span lang="EN">ICT-DIT-3003-1.1</span></strong><strong><span lang="EN">&nbsp;</span>TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have&nbsp;achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$800</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$72.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$472.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$312.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2022015539" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2022015539" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2022015539" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2022015539) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=56671;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a journey to become a Google Professional Cloud Security Engineer with our comprehensive certification prep course. This course is meticulously designed for IT professionals aiming to deepen their expertise in cloud security on the Google Cloud Platform (GCP). You''ll gain in-depth knowledge of GCP''s core services, security best practices, and the latest strategies in securing cloud environments. Our curriculum covers critical aspects of cloud security, including identity and access management, data protection, and network security, providing you with the skills needed to design and implement secure infrastructure on GCP.</p>\n<p>Our expert instructors, equipped with real-world experience, will guide you through interactive sessions, practical exercises, and up-to-date course materials. The course is structured to not only prepare you for the Google Professional Cloud Security Engineer certification exam but also to enhance your practical skills for immediate application in your current or future roles. Whether you''re an IT security specialist, a cloud engineer, or an aspiring security professional, this course is your stepping stone to achieving certification and excelling in the realm of cloud security. Enroll now to secure your spot and advance your career in this rapidly evolving field.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses and official Autodesk Certificate of Completion after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n<h2>Register for Google Cloud Certification</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://cloud.google.com/learn/certification?hl=en" title="Google Cloud Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;We are&nbsp; Kryterion Authorized Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course.</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=57131;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a journey to become a Google Professional Cloud Security Engineer with our comprehensive certification prep course. This course is meticulously designed for IT professionals aiming to deepen their expertise in cloud security on the Google Cloud Platform (GCP). You''ll gain in-depth knowledge of GCP''s core services, security best practices, and the latest strategies in securing cloud environments. Our curriculum covers critical aspects of cloud security, including identity and access management, data protection, and network security, providing you with the skills needed to design and implement secure infrastructure on GCP.</p>\n<p>Our expert instructors, equipped with real-world experience, will guide you through interactive sessions, practical exercises, and up-to-date course materials. The course is structured to not only prepare you for the Google Professional Cloud Security Engineer certification exam but also to enhance your practical skills for immediate application in your current or future roles. Whether you''re an IT security specialist, a cloud engineer, or an aspiring security professional, this course is your stepping stone to achieving certification and excelling in the realm of cloud security. Enroll now to secure your spot and advance your career in this rapidly evolving field.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses and official Autodesk Certificate of Completion after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n<h2>Register for Google Cloud Certification</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://cloud.google.com/learn/certification?hl=en" title="Google Cloud Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n' WHERE value_id=57789;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>In this dynamic course, participants will dive into the world of Generative AI, specifically tailored for creative design using Adobe Photoshop and Firefly. The curriculum is designed to equip learners with cutting-edge skills in integrating AI technologies into graphic design workflows. You''ll explore how Generative AI can transform your creative process, enabling the generation of unique and complex designs that would be challenging or time-consuming to create manually.</p>\n<p>The course not only focuses on the technical aspects of using Generative AI in Photoshop and Firefly but also emphasizes the artistic side of leveraging AI to enhance creativity. Participants will gain hands-on experience in applying AI-powered tools for image manipulation, pattern generation, and artistic effects. Whether you are a professional designer looking to incorporate AI into your work, or an enthusiast eager to explore the intersection of technology and art, this course will provide you with the knowledge and skills to push the boundaries of digital design.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>For WSQ funding, please checkout the details at&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/wsq-generative-ai-gai-visuals-in-photoshop-and-firefly.html" title="WSQ - Generative AI (GAI) Visuals in Photoshop and Firefly">WSQ - Generative AI (GAI) Visuals in Photoshop and Firefly</a></span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=58262;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>&lt;p&gt;In this dynamic course, participants will dive into the world of Generative AI, specifically tailored for creative design using Adobe Photoshop and Firefly. The curriculum is designed to equip learners with cutting-edge skills in integrating AI technologies into graphic design workflows. You''ll explore how Generative AI can transform your creative process, enabling the generation of unique and complex designs that would be challenging or time-consuming to create manually.&lt;/p&gt;<br />&lt;p&gt;The course not only focuses on the technical aspects of using Generative AI in Photoshop and Firefly but also emphasizes the artistic side of leveraging AI to enhance creativity. Participants will gain hands-on experience in applying AI-powered tools for image manipulation, pattern generation, and artistic effects. Whether you are a professional designer looking to incorporate AI into your work, or an enthusiast eager to explore the intersection of technology and art, this course will provide you with the knowledge and skills to push the boundaries of digital design.&lt;/p&gt;</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after attendance.</p>' WHERE value_id=58289;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>In the ever-evolving landscape of networking, the Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) stands as a hallmark of foundational proficiency. Our CCNA Exam Preparation course is tailored to ensure that aspiring network professionals grasp the intricate details of networking, setting them on the path to certification success. We demystify the complexities of networking, making it accessible and understandable for all.</p>\n<p>From routing and switching to network security and automation, our course encompasses every domain of the CCNA syllabus. With a blend of theoretical concepts and hands-on labs, learners will gain practical experience, ensuring they''re well-equipped to tackle real-world challenges post-certification. Whether you''re kickstarting your networking career or aiming to solidify your foundational knowledge, our CCNA Exam Prep is your trusted companion on this journey.<br />High Resolution USB Camera</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong>&nbsp;- Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Certification</strong>&nbsp;-&nbsp;The participant will be able to attempt the 200-301 Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) certification exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) accreditation from CISCO. This certification validates a participant''s proficiency in configuring, operating, and troubleshooting medium-sized networks.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://home.pearsonvue.com/cisco.aspx" title="Cisco Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>. We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center.&nbsp;Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available</p>\n<p>For WSQ funding, please checkout the details at&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/wsq-certified-network-associate-ccna.html" title="WSQ - Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA)">WSQ - Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA)</a></span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=66630;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>In the ever-evolving landscape of networking, the Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) stands as a hallmark of foundational proficiency. Our CCNA Exam Preparation course is tailored to ensure that aspiring network professionals grasp the intricate details of networking, setting them on the path to certification success. We demystify the complexities of networking, making it accessible and understandable for all.</p>\n<p>From routing and switching to network security and automation, our course encompasses every domain of the CCNA syllabus. With a blend of theoretical concepts and hands-on labs, learners will gain practical experience, ensuring they''re well-equipped to tackle real-world challenges post-certification. Whether you''re kickstarting your networking career or aiming to solidify your foundational knowledge, our CCNA Exam Prep is your trusted companion on this journey.</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong>&nbsp;- Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Certification</strong>&nbsp;-&nbsp;The participant will be able to attempt the 200-301 Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) certification exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) accreditation from CISCO. This certification validates a participant''s proficiency in configuring, operating, and troubleshooting medium-sized networks.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://home.pearsonvue.com/cisco.aspx" title="Cisco Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>. We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center.&nbsp;Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>' WHERE value_id=70474;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>The Certified Kubernetes Application Developer (CKAD) Training equips developers with the skills needed to design, build, and deploy cloud-native applications on Kubernetes. This course covers essential Kubernetes concepts, including multi-container pod design, workload resources, persistent storage, and deployment strategies like blue/green and canary releases. You will learn how to use Helm and Kustomize for package management, perform rolling updates, and manage API deprecations effectively.</p>\n<p>Additionally, the course dives into application observability, security, and networking in Kubernetes. You will explore debugging techniques, health probes, logging, authentication, role-based access control (RBAC), and resource limits. Hands-on practice with Ingress rules, NetworkPolicies, ConfigMaps, and Secrets ensures a deep understanding of real-world Kubernetes application development. This training prepares you for the CKAD certification, advancing your career in DevOps, cloud engineering, and software development.</p>\n\n\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>' WHERE value_id=70634;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Master the fundamentals of Codex CLI and unlock the power of agentic vibe coding to transform your software development workflow. This comprehensive course equips you with the essential skills to set up, configure, and leverage Codex CLI for intelligent code navigation, context management, and automated development tasks. Learn how to create structured project instruction files, manage session memory, and execute complex shell tasks with precision — all through an AI-powered command-line interface that understands your codebase.</p>\n<p>Advance your capabilities with hands-on training in agentic development workflows, custom skill creation, and MCP integration for connecting to external tools and services. From planning-first strategies and reasoning modes to real-world GitHub automation, parallel development using Git branches, and browser workflow validation, this course prepares you to build, test, debug, and deploy applications with unprecedented speed and efficiency. Whether you are refactoring legacy code, converting notebooks into deployable apps, or managing multiple agent sessions, you will gain the practical expertise to harness AI-assisted coding at a professional level.</p>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p>TBD</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this class.</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=70739;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive into the profound capabilities of Machine Learning on the Google Cloud Platform with Tertiary Courses. Our in-depth curriculum sheds light on the myriad of hosting options available, be it Serverless, container-based, or via virtual machines, ensuring that you''re equipped to make informed decisions tailored to your specific needs. Grasp the essence of enabling GCP''s ML AIs and hone your skills in preparing data through Cloud Dataflow and Dataprep, pivotal for any robust ML pipeline.</p>\n<p>As we advance, delve into the intriguing world of modeling predictions for diverse media including images, video, text-to-speech, and cloud translation. Our hands-on approach ensures you''re adept at employing AutoML for streamlined ML tasks. We further delve into intricate machine learning and deep learning modules, wrapping up with a comprehensive understanding of modern ML architectures. This course is an indispensable asset for those enthusiastic about harnessing the full potential of machine learning on GCP.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n<h2>Register for Google Cloud Certification</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://cloud.google.com/learn/certification?hl=en" title="Google Cloud Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;We are&nbsp; Kryterion Authorized Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=70911;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive into the world of UI/UX design with our specialized Adobe XD Training. As the realm of digital design continuously evolves, it becomes crucial for professionals to stay updated with the latest tools and techniques. Adobe XD, a pioneer in the UI/UX design landscape, offers designers an integrated platform to craft, animate, and bring their visions to life. This course is meticulously curated to ensure participants gain a deep understanding of XD''s multifaceted features, making it an essential toolkit for any designer''s repertoire.</p>\n<p>Our training commences by introducing attendees to the intuitive XD interface, emphasizing seamless navigation techniques. Participants will explore the integration of prominent design tools like Photoshop, Illustrator, and Sketch with XD, amplifying their design capabilities. By harnessing the Repeat Grid feature, designers can effortlessly replicate elements, saving invaluable time. The course further delves into the realm of animations, teaching users how to add dynamic elements to their designs. Additionally, the innovative voice interactions feature of XD will be explored, paving the way for futuristic design solutions. The training culminates by guiding participants through the exporting process, ensuring designs are ready for any platform or medium. By the end of the sessions, participants will be well-versed in using Adobe XD, elevating their UI/UX design game manifold.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p class="p1">No funding is available for this course.</p>\n<p>For WSQ funding, please checkout the details at&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/wsq-user-interface-design-adobe-xd.html" title="WSQ - Interactive UI Design with Adobe XD: From Wireframes to Prototypes">WSQ - Interactive UI Design with Adobe XD: From Wireframes to Prototypes</a></span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>\n</div>\n' WHERE value_id=70964;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive into the profound capabilities of Machine Learning on the Google Cloud Platform with Tertiary Courses. Our in-depth curriculum sheds light on the myriad of hosting options available, be it Serverless, container-based, or via virtual machines, ensuring that you''re equipped to make informed decisions tailored to your specific needs. Grasp the essence of enabling GCP''s ML AIs and hone your skills in preparing data through Cloud Dataflow and Dataprep, pivotal for any robust ML pipeline.</p>\n<p>As we advance, delve into the intriguing world of modeling predictions for diverse media including images, video, text-to-speech, and cloud translation. Our hands-on approach ensures you''re adept at employing AutoML for streamlined ML tasks. We further delve into intricate machine learning and deep learning modules, wrapping up with a comprehensive understanding of modern ML architectures. This course is an indispensable asset for those enthusiastic about harnessing the full potential of machine learning on GCP.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Register for Google Cloud Certification</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://cloud.google.com/learn/certification?hl=en" title="Google Cloud Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>' WHERE value_id=71358;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive into the world of UI/UX design with our specialized Adobe XD Training. As the realm of digital design continuously evolves, it becomes crucial for professionals to stay updated with the latest tools and techniques. Adobe XD, a pioneer in the UI/UX design landscape, offers designers an integrated platform to craft, animate, and bring their visions to life. This course is meticulously curated to ensure participants gain a deep understanding of XD''s multifaceted features, making it an essential toolkit for any designer''s repertoire.</p>\n<p>Our training commences by introducing attendees to the intuitive XD interface, emphasizing seamless navigation techniques. Participants will explore the integration of prominent design tools like Photoshop, Illustrator, and Sketch with XD, amplifying their design capabilities. By harnessing the Repeat Grid feature, designers can effortlessly replicate elements, saving invaluable time. The course further delves into the realm of animations, teaching users how to add dynamic elements to their designs. Additionally, the innovative voice interactions feature of XD will be explored, paving the way for futuristic design solutions. The training culminates by guiding participants through the exporting process, ensuring designs are ready for any platform or medium. By the end of the sessions, participants will be well-versed in using Adobe XD, elevating their UI/UX design game manifold.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>' WHERE value_id=71409;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Unlock the power of data-driven narratives with our Data Storytelling with Tableau course. This program commences by focusing on the essentials: designing compelling storyboards that lay the groundwork for effective data communication. Our expert-guided training ensures that participants not only understand but also skillfully apply various storytelling techniques to make their data speak volumes.</p>\n<p>Beyond mere theory, the course accentuates on knowing your audience and crafting visual narratives that resonate. By integrating effective visuals, participants will learn to convey complex data points with clarity and impact. The program culminates with practical sessions, enabling attendees to distill complex datasets into clear, compelling, and actionable stories. Whether you''re presenting to stakeholders or aiming to influence business decisions, mastering data storytelling with Tableau arms you with the tools to do it persuasively.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p class="p1">No funding is available for this course.</p>\n<p>For WSQ funding, please checkout the details at&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/wsq-data-storytelling-tableau.html" title="WSQ Tableau Data Storytelling Course">WSQ - Tableau Data Storytelling Course</a></span></p>\n</div>\n' WHERE value_id=71532;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Unlock the capabilities of Tableau for visual storytelling in our comprehensive WSQ-endorsed course. We cover everything from the basics of data import and cleaning to crafting advanced interactive dashboards. You''ll learn how to use Tableau''s extensive set of tools through hands-on exercises and real-world examples, ensuring you acquire practical skills to transform raw data into insightful visual narratives.</p>\n<p>By the end of this course, you&rsquo;ll be proficient in using Tableau for a variety of data visualization needs. You''ll be able to create compelling dashboards that communicate complex data in a straightforward, insightful manner. This course is perfect for analysts, business professionals, or anyone keen on leveraging data to make informed decisions and to tell powerful stories with data.</p>\n<h2>Course Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Apply basic Tableau features for displaying information.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Synthesise various plots to present data visually.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Transform data to create informative and dynamic data display.</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Create dashboards and scorecards to display internal as well as external benchmark data.</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Apply calculation and parameter to create interactive graphics, visuals and technical features into the data presentation.</li>\n<li>LO6:&nbsp;Perform analytics to communicate limitations of data and interpretations of findings.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/10eix46qjeKF1m_OFTmzBSyqvrE73lLmS/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ &ndash; Data Visualisation with Tableau Course Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ &ndash; Data Visualisation with Tableau Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Data Visualization ICT-DIT-3006-1.1 TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have&nbsp;&nbsp;achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$750.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$67.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$442.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$292.50</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover up out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2020503177" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used.&nbsp;<a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020503177" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding. Please inform us if you intend to use your PSEA funding .</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020503177" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2020503177) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=74823;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Unlock the full potential of Adobe Captivate in your eLearning ventures with this essential training. Dive deep into creating robust, responsive projects while ensuring flexibility with the adept use of Fluid Boxes. Familiarize yourself with the essentials of previewing, building, and concluding projects seamlessly.</p>\n<p>Enhance your eLearning content with techniques on editing master slides, programming buttons, and selecting the optimal file format. With the addition of closed captions and voiceovers, make your content accessible and engaging. Furthermore, expand your horizons by exploring integration with other eLearning platforms, including the widely used SCORMs, ensuring a comprehensive grasp of today''s eLearning tools.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=76308;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Robotic process automation (RPA) is revolutionizing business processes everywhere. Automation Anywhere is enterprise-grade RPA software that puts automation in the hands of your workers&mdash;without sacrificing reliability or security. This course introduces learners to the potential for automating repetitive tasks using Automation Anywhere. Review the components of Automation Anywhere architecture, and then discover how to create a bot step by step. You can study the three case studies included with the course to better understand how the automation process can be customized for your business.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p class="p1">No funding is available for this course.</p>\n<p>For WSQ funding, please checkout the details at&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/wsq-rpa-automation-anywhere.html" title="WSQ - Applications Integration with Robotic Process Automation (RPA)">WSQ - Applications Integration with Robotic Process Automation (RPA) </a></span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=76332;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Unlock the power of data-driven narratives with our Data Storytelling with Tableau course. This program commences by focusing on the essentials: designing compelling storyboards that lay the groundwork for effective data communication. Our expert-guided training ensures that participants not only understand but also skillfully apply various storytelling techniques to make their data speak volumes.</p>\n<p>Beyond mere theory, the course accentuates on knowing your audience and crafting visual narratives that resonate. By integrating effective visuals, participants will learn to convey complex data points with clarity and impact. The program culminates with practical sessions, enabling attendees to distill complex datasets into clear, compelling, and actionable stories. Whether you''re presenting to stakeholders or aiming to influence business decisions, mastering data storytelling with Tableau arms you with the tools to do it persuasively.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n' WHERE value_id=78617;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a journey to mastering the Google Cloud Platform with our Google Associate Cloud Engineer Certification Exam Prep course. This comprehensive course is meticulously designed to equip you with the knowledge and skills needed to excel in the Google Associate Cloud Engineer Certification Exam, ensuring you are well-prepared to tackle the challenges of the exam and achieve certification success.</p>\n<p>Our course covers all the essential topics and provides practical insights to help you understand the intricacies of the Google Cloud Platform. With expert instructors and a curriculum tailored to the exam''s requirements, you will gain a deep understanding of the platform, enhancing your cloud skills and opening up new career opportunities. Enroll now and take the first step towards becoming a certified Google Associate Cloud Engineer.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n\n<h2>Register for Google Cloud Certification</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://cloud.google.com/learn/certification?hl=en" title="Google Cloud Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;We are&nbsp; Kryterion Authorized Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=82905;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a journey to mastering the Google Cloud Platform with our Google Associate Cloud Engineer Certification Exam Prep course. This comprehensive course is meticulously designed to equip you with the knowledge and skills needed to excel in the Google Associate Cloud Engineer Certification Exam, ensuring you are well-prepared to tackle the challenges of the exam and achieve certification success.</p>\n<p>Our course covers all the essential topics and provides practical insights to help you understand the intricacies of the Google Cloud Platform. With expert instructors and a curriculum tailored to the exam''s requirements, you will gain a deep understanding of the platform, enhancing your cloud skills and opening up new career opportunities. Enroll now and take the first step towards becoming a certified Google Associate Cloud Engineer.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Register for Google Cloud Certification</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://cloud.google.com/learn/certification?hl=en" title="Google Cloud Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>' WHERE value_id=82957;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive into the intricate world of pattern recognition and machine learning with our WSQ-accredited course. This course is structured to take you from the essentials of R programming to the complexities of machine learning algorithms. You will learn to deploy pattern recognition techniques for data classification, delve into clustering methods, and explore predictive analytics. Real-world examples and projects are integrated into the curriculum for hands-on learning.</p>\n<p>Whether you''re a seasoned data scientist or a beginner eager to expand your skill set, this course is designed to equip you with the knowledge needed for the evolving field of data analytics. You''ll leave with practical experience in applying machine learning algorithms using R, positioning you at the forefront of today&rsquo;s data-driven landscape. Upgrade your analytics skills and stay ahead of the curve with our specialized training.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p><span>By end of the course, learners should be able to</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Model pattern recognition problems suitable for machine learning.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Apply supervised regression techniques to predict pattern in the data.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Apply supervised classification techniques to classify pattern in the data.</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Apply unsupervised clustering techniques to cluster patterns and detect anomaly in the data.</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Apply principal component analysis as alternative method to detect pattern in the data.</li>\n<li>LO6:&nbsp;Apply deep neural network and CNN models for visual recognition.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1dUcGtlRv32aRlG44fN03jEwqrFAOixyF/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Pattern Recognition and Machine Learning with R Course Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Pattern Recognition and Machine Learning with R Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Pattern Recognition Systems ICT-DIT-4026-1.1 TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$750.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$67.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$442.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$292.50</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2020504357" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020504357" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding. Please inform us if you intend to use your PSEA funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020504357" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2020504357) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=83172;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Unlock the potential of visual data with our WSQ-endorsed Computer Vision for Beginners course. This foundational course is designed to introduce you to the basics of computer vision, from image analysis to object detection. Through hands-on exercises, you will learn how to manipulate images and videos using a variety of techniques and tools, laying the groundwork for more advanced studies in the field.</p>\n<p>By the end of this course, you''ll have a strong understanding of the core principles of computer vision. Whether you aim to deepen your knowledge in data science or apply visual data in your professional field, this course serves as your stepping stone. You''ll be well-equipped to understand, interpret, and make data-driven decisions based on visual information.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Understand basic vision systems concepts and applications</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Apply basic computer vision techniques</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Implement image classification</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Implement object detection and video analytics</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Evaluate edge and cloud-based computer vision systems</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Material</h2>\n<p>A RPI kit set will be given out to trainee for training use. The kit set consists of the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Raspberry Pi 4 4GB RAM Board</li>\n<li>Power Adaptor</li>\n<li>16G microSD Card</li>\n<li>HDMI Cable</li>\n<li>USB Camera</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1_oZ2R_g8rdGuamavurzS-pJyXY5NBDe0/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Computer Vision for Beginners Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Computer Vision for Beginners Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Computer Vision Technology ICT-DIT-4022-1.1 TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$1000</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$90.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$590.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$390.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2020504540" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020504540" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding. Please inform us if you intend to use your PSEA funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020504540" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2020504540) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=84898;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Ready to disrupt the traditional business landscape? Our course on Business Innovation with Internet-of-Things (IoT) is your key to unlocking new avenues for growth and efficiency. Learn how to seamlessly integrate IoT technologies into your business model, from improving operations with smart solutions to gaining actionable insights through data analytics. By the end of this course, you''ll be equipped to make strategic decisions that drive digital transformation and create a sustainable competitive advantage.</p>\n<p>But we take you beyond just understanding IoT technologies. Dive into real-world applications and case studies that demonstrate how IoT can solve specific business challenges. Master the art of crafting an IoT strategy that aligns with your business objectives, mitigates risks, and offers a significant ROI. Whether you''re looking to optimize existing processes or develop new revenue streams, this course will provide you with the expertise to lead your business into the future.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p style="display: inline !important;">LO1: Compare current business model with IoT business model</p>\n</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Explore potential opportunities for using IoT</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Identify how IoT works</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Weigh the costs-benefits of adopting IoT</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Implement business innovation processes with IoT</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1pGfT5q8gx2Cdf2o6V8pArcE7aUGjzjMv/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Business Innovation with Internet-of-Things (IoT) Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Business Innovation with Internet-of-Things (IoT) Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Business Innovation ICT-SNA-4003-1.1 TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$350</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$31.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$206.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$136.50</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2020504706" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020504706" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=85134;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Robotic process automation (RPA) is revolutionizing business processes everywhere. Automation Anywhere is enterprise-grade RPA software that puts automation in the hands of your workers—without sacrificing reliability or security. This course introduces learners to the potential for automating repetitive tasks using Automation Anywhere. Review the components of Automation Anywhere architecture, and then discover how to create a bot step by step. You can study the three case studies included with the course to better understand how the automation process can be customized for your business.</p>\n\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n\n' WHERE value_id=85246;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Ready to revolutionize the way you work? Dive into our WSQ Robotics Process Automation (RPA) course tailored for beginners. Learn how to automate repetitive and time-consuming tasks with the power of UIPath. You''ll get hands-on experience in workflow design, UIPath Studio, and automating processes across various software platforms. By mastering these basics, you''ll gain the skills needed to significantly enhance productivity and operational efficiency.</p>\n<p>But we go beyond just the fundamentals. The course delves into more advanced aspects of RPA, such as error handling, debugging, and orchestrating more complex automation sequences. This comprehensive approach ensures you are well-prepared to tackle real-world challenges in workflow automation. Whether you''re a business professional seeking to optimize processes or a tech enthusiast looking to enter the booming field of RPA, this course sets you on the path to success.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p><span>By end of the course, learners should be able to</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Determine the best practices of RPA.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Build full functional RPA robots.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Design and validate various automation processes.</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Debug RPA workflows</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Deploy and optimise RPA</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/11TN0YQqvnwG3it6YfkJDXVdafUpBLSPt/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Robotics Process Automation (RPA) for Beginners Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Robotics Process Automation (RPA) for Beginners Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Self-Learning Systems ICT-DIT-4028-1.1 TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$750.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$67.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$442.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$292.50</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2020504808" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020504808" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding. Please inform us if you intend to use your PSEA funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020504808" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2020504808) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=85424;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Unlock the transformative power of artificial intelligence with our WSQ-endorsed Practical Reinforcement Learning for Beginners course. As one of the most dynamic fields in AI, reinforcement learning offers unparalleled opportunities for problem-solving and decision-making. This course guides you through the foundational algorithms and techniques, all while offering hands-on experience through real-world projects. You''ll develop the skills to implement effective learning agents in various environments.</p>\n<p>Upon completing the course, you''ll be proficient in the core concepts and applications of reinforcement learning. From designing smart agents to navigating complex data sets, this course equips you with the know-how to apply reinforcement learning in practical scenarios, making it an essential stepping stone for anyone aiming to specialize in AI and data science.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>By end of the course, learners should be able to</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Understand and apply the fundamental concepts of reinforcement learning</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Use RL on OpenAI Gym</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Build value-based reinforcement learning systems</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Build model-based reinforcement learning systems</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Build policy-based reinforcement learning systems</li>\n<li>LO6:&nbsp;Assess reinforcement learning systems and suggest more advanced reinforcement learning systems</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jP40H-KFIstsvXhFQETWZzyDwgLM5U2z/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ &ndash; Practical Reinforcement Learning for Beginners Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ &ndash; Practical Reinforcement Learning for Beginners Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Self-Learning Systems ICT-DIT-5028-1.1 TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$750.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$67.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$442.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$292.50</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2020504974" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020504974" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding. Please inform us if you intend to use your PSEA funding .</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020504974" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2020504974) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=85557;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Upgrade your financial management capabilities with our WSQ Quickbooks Accounting System for Small and Medium Enterprises course. Designed to meet the unique accounting needs of SMEs, this course offers hands-on training on using Quickbooks for various accounting tasks, including invoicing, expense tracking, and financial reporting. You''ll acquire the skills to set up and manage accounts, monitor cash flows, and generate accurate financial statements, empowering you to make data-driven decisions for business growth.</p>\n<p>Unleash the full potential of Quickbooks to streamline your SME''s accounting processes. The course covers key functionalities such as accounts payable and receivable, inventory management, and payroll processing. Whether you''re a business owner, an accountant, or someone involved in financial management, this course provides you with a comprehensive understanding of Quickbooks, enabling you to optimize financial operations, maintain compliance, and drive business success.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Configure and import relevant data to Quickbooks accounting system.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Input data to Quickbooks.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Compute GST for expenses and invoices.</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Generate financial and accounting reports.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/16KNSb6VyI0CLv5ASVMeru7y5VPx0EJsT/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Quickbooks Accounting System for Small and Medium Enterprises Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Quickbooks Accounting System for Small and Medium Enterprises Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Accounting and Tax Systems ACC-ICT-4001-1.1 TSC</strong> under Accounting Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$350.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$31.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$206.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$136.50</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2020505113" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020505113" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=86292;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive into the world of data analytics and visualization with our comprehensive WSQ-endorsed course on Power BI. This course is designed to teach you how to turn complex data into compelling visual stories. You''ll learn to navigate the Power BI interface, connect to various data sources, and create interactive dashboards. Practical exercises and real-world examples are integrated into the curriculum, ensuring you''ll gain actionable skills.</p>\n<p>By the end of this course, you''ll be proficient in using Power BI to analyze data, create visualizations, and develop interactive dashboards that can inform business decisions. Whether you''re a business professional looking to upskill, a data enthusiast, or someone in a decision-making role, this course equips you with the tools and knowledge to make data-driven decisions effectively.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Perform data transformation techniques using Power BI</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Create data visualization to portray data trends and correlations</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Develop dashboards and scoreboards</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Create dynamics data visualization</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Create data model for strategic visualization and mapping</li>\n<li>LO6:&nbsp;Perform data analytics and queries with DAX</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1HpDy83igUr0gTmOcDv64AmUXLihVpoZm/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Data Analytics and Visualization with Power BI Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Data Analytics and Visualization with Power BI Course Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Data Visualization MED-DIT-4006-1.1 TSC</strong> under Media Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$800</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$72.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$472.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$312.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2020505444"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020505444" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding. Please inform us if you intend to use your PSEA funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020505444" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2020505444) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=88100;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on the fascinating journey of turning raw data into meaningful stories with our WSQ-endorsed course on Data Storytelling with Tableau. Learn how to craft compelling narratives by leveraging Tableau''s suite of data visualization tools. Our course covers techniques like contextual data representation, storytelling with dashboards, and how to utilize various visual elements for impact. Hands-on exercises and case studies are integrated into the curriculum, ensuring you gain both the theoretical knowledge and practical skills needed for effective data storytelling.</p>\n<p>By the completion of this course, you''ll be adept at creating engaging, insightful data stories using Tableau. You&rsquo;ll learn how to select the right visualization techniques for different types of data and audiences, how to build dashboards that tell a story, and how to interpret data in a way that resonates with stakeholders. Whether you''re a data analyst, a marketing professional, or anyone in between, this course provides you with the tools to communicate data-driven insights effectively.</p>\n<h2>Course Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Utilize Tableau for data visualization&nbsp;</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Identify trends and patterns from data</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Develop dashboards and stories for data storytelling</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Present stories to stakeholders and review with subject matter experts</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Design interactive visualizations for data storytelling</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1o3NPo5d-bMxd6tOeFI3TUUqUYULRJSdf/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Data Storytelling with Tableau Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Data Storytelling with Tableau Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Data Storytelling ICT-DIT-4006-1.1 TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$750.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$67.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$442.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$292.50</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover up out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2020505550" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020505550" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding. Please inform us if you intend to use your PSEA funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020505550" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2020505550) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=88217;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a groundbreaking journey with our WSQ-endorsed Pattern Recognition with Pytorch course. This course will introduce you to the complexities of recognizing patterns in data sets, utilizing Pytorch as the main framework. Through real-world examples and hands-on projects, you''ll get to grips with neural networks, image recognition, and various machine learning algorithms, sharpening your skills in data analysis.</p>\n<p>Upon completion of the course, you''ll be fully equipped to interpret complex data structures and predict future patterns using Pytorch. This course is your stepping stone to becoming a specialist in machine learning and data analysis, with a particular focus on pattern recognition techniques.</p>\n<h2>Course Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Assess various machine learning techniques across different application domains.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Apply machine learning techniques to regression and classification problems.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Solve temporal sequential problem using recurrent neural network.</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Build pattern recognition systems using convolutional neural network.</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Apply machine learning techniques to signal processing.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1XB6QTNcySrRosnwgIPrBzkBRBUVdOfyN/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ &ndash; Building Advanced Machine Learning and AI Solutions with Pytorch Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ &ndash; Building Advanced Machine Learning and AI Solutions with Pytorch Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Pattern Recognition Systems ICT-DIT-5026-1.1 TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$750.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$67.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$442.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$292.50</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover up out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2020505815" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020505815" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding. Please inform us if you intend to use your PSEA funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020505815" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2020505815) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=88880;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Take your skills in visual data analysis to new heights with our WSQ-endorsed course on Image and Video Processing with OpenCV. This in-depth course covers essential topics like object detection, face recognition, and real-time video analysis using OpenCV''s powerful libraries. Through hands-on exercises and case studies, you''ll learn how to process and analyze visual data, gaining the skills to tackle a range of image and video processing challenges.</p>\n<p>By the end of this course, you&rsquo;ll have acquired a strong foundation in image and video processing using OpenCV. Whether you are an aspiring data scientist, a developer interested in computer vision, or a professional in fields requiring visual data interpretation, this course will provide you with the tools to understand, analyze, and make informed decisions based on visual data.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Understand basic vision systems concepts and applications</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Apply image processing with OpenCV</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Implement feature extraction with OpenCV</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Apply machine learning based computer vision methods</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Implement video analytics algorithms with OpenCV</li>\n<li>LO6:&nbsp;Evaluate edge vs cloud-based computer vision systems</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Material</h2>\n<p>A RPI kit set will be loan out to trainee for training use. The kit set on loan will be as follows:<a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1T-6DdIYPrIAQSO1e6UIQ-Y2a2ezg4PEl/view?usp=sharing" title="NodeMCU IoT Starter Kit" target="_blank">&nbsp;</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Raspberry Pi 4 Model B 4GB</li>\n<li>16G microSD Card preloaded with Raspberry OS.</li>\n<li>Raspberry Pi Power Adaptor</li>\n<li>USB Camera</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1Ac7cV-DFv3yA--TYuCt3BZQcgI4dNo85/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Image and Video Processing with OpenCV Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Image and Video Processing with OpenCV Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Computer Vision Technology ICT-DIT-4022-1.1 TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$900</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$81.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$531.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$351.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2020505925" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020505925" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding. Please inform us if you intend to use your PSEA funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2020505925" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2020505925) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=89053;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Elevate your understanding of Robotic Process Automation with our UIPath RPA Essential Training. This meticulously crafted course provides a deep dive into core UIPath operations, offering participants a robust foundation in Control Flow Scripting, and a comprehensive grasp of automating emails, web interactions, and file operations.</p>\n<p>Beyond the basics, the training delves into sophisticated realms of RPA, including proficient error handling techniques, leveraging the UIPath Orchestrator for centralized robot management, and exploring the potential of cognitive activities. Whether you are a novice or a professional seeking to upgrade your RPA skills, this course provides the expertise you need.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n<p>For WSQ funding, please checkout the details at&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/wsq-rpa-course.html" title="WSQ Robotics Process Automation (RPA) for Beginners">WSQ Robotics Process Automation (RPA) for Beginners</a></span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=90502;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Elevate your understanding of Robotic Process Automation with our UIPath RPA Essential Training. This meticulously crafted course provides a deep dive into core UIPath operations, offering participants a robust foundation in Control Flow Scripting, and a comprehensive grasp of automating emails, web interactions, and file operations.</p>\n<p>Beyond the basics, the training delves into sophisticated realms of RPA, including proficient error handling techniques, leveraging the UIPath Orchestrator for centralized robot management, and exploring the potential of cognitive activities. Whether you are a novice or a professional seeking to upgrade your RPA skills, this course provides the expertise you need.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n' WHERE value_id=90546;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Algorithmic trading relies on computer programs that execute algorithms to automate some or all elements of a trading strategy. Algorithms are a sequence of steps or rules designed to achieve a goal. They can take many forms and facilitate optimization throughout the investment process, from idea generation to asset allocation, trade execution, and risk management.</p>\n<p>Machine learning (ML) and Deep Learning (DL) involves algorithms that learn rules or patterns from data to achieve a goal such as minimizing a prediction error.&nbsp;&nbsp;ML and DL algorithms can extract information from data to support or automate key investment activities. This course will teach the basis of ML and DL used for trading.</p>\n\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n\n\n\n' WHERE value_id=92778;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Algorithmic trading relies on computer programs that execute algorithms to automate some or all elements of a trading strategy. Algorithms are a sequence of steps or rules designed to achieve a goal. They can take many forms and facilitate optimisation throughout the investment process, from idea generation to asset allocation, trade execution, and risk management.</p>\n<p>Machine learning (ML) and Deep Learning (DL) involves algorithms that learn rules or patterns from data to achieve a goal such as minimizing a prediction error.&nbsp;&nbsp;ML and DL algorithms can extract information from data to support or automate key investment activities. This course will teach the basis of ML and DL used for trading.</p>\n\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n<p>For IBF funding, please checkout the details at&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/ibf-machine-learning-101-for-financial-trading.html" title="Machine Learning 101 for Financial Trading (IBF Funded)">Machine Learning 101 for Financial Trading (IBF Funded)</a></span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=92859;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a creative journey with WSQ''s Digital Image Production with Photoshop course. Gain expertise in the most sought-after image editing tools, from the fundamentals to advanced techniques. The course covers essential Photoshop features such as layers, filters, color adjustments, and photo manipulation, equipping you with the skills to excel in the field of graphic design.</p>\n<p>The course adopts a practical approach, combining instructional modules with hands-on exercises and real-world projects. These projects allow you to apply your newly acquired Photoshop skills in various industry-relevant scenarios. By the end of the course, you''ll possess the competence to produce top-quality digital images, whether for personal use or professional purposes.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Apply basic Photoshop techniques for digital imagery</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Improve Photoshop techniques through experimentation.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Evaluate the digital imaging technique through adaptation</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1iKGFOuUlvpktY5dAnhbvFDjZF3NGIduE/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Professional Digital Image Editing with Photoshop Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Professional Digital Image Editing with Photoshop Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guidelines of <strong> Digital Image Production RET-DNI-4003-1.1</strong> TSC under Retail Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$690.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$62.10</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$407.10</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$269.10</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover of out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2021003585" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2021003585" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2021003585" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2021003585) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=94435;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a journey to becoming a Certified Information Systems Auditor with our comprehensive CISA Exam Prep course. This course is meticulously designed for IT professionals aiming to deepen their expertise in IT governance, risk management, and information systems control. Through our expert-led training, you''ll gain a thorough understanding of the CISA certification requirements and the latest industry practices. Enhance your skills in identifying IT risks and implementing effective controls, ensuring you are well-prepared to tackle the CISA exam with confidence.</p>\n<p>Our CISA Exam Prep course not only prepares you for the exam but also equips you with practical knowledge applicable in the real world. Delve into key areas such as cybersecurity, IT auditing, and information systems management. Our interactive course modules and hands-on exercises provide an immersive learning experience, ensuring you grasp complex concepts with ease. Whether you''re looking to advance in your current role or pivot to a career in IT auditing and cybersecurity, this course lays the foundation for your success in the dynamic field of information systems.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.isaca.org/credentialing/cisa title="CISACertification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n\n\n<div style=" width: 80%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n</div>\n\n' WHERE value_id=94481;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a journey to becoming a Certified Information Systems Auditor with our comprehensive CISA Exam Prep course. This course is meticulously designed for IT professionals aiming to deepen their expertise in IT governance, risk management, and information systems control. Through our expert-led training, you''ll gain a thorough understanding of the CISA certification requirements and the latest industry practices. Enhance your skills in identifying IT risks and implementing effective controls, ensuring you are well-prepared to tackle the CISA exam with confidence.</p>\n<p>Our CISA Exam Prep course not only prepares you for the exam but also equips you with practical knowledge applicable in the real world. Delve into key areas such as cybersecurity, IT auditing, and information systems management. Our interactive course modules and hands-on exercises provide an immersive learning experience, ensuring you grasp complex concepts with ease. Whether you''re looking to advance in your current role or pivot to a career in IT auditing and cybersecurity, this course lays the foundation for your success in the dynamic field of information systems.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.isaca.org/credentialing/cisa title="CISACertification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n\n\n' WHERE value_id=94512;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a journey to success with our PL-600 Microsoft Power Platform Solution Architect Exam Prep course. This meticulously crafted course is tailored to provide you with an in-depth understanding of the Microsoft Power Platform, equipping you with the knowledge and skills required to excel in the PL-600 exam. Our expert instructors will guide you through the intricacies of designing and implementing solutions on the Microsoft Power Platform, ensuring you are well-prepared to tackle the challenges of the exam and emerge victorious.</p>\n<p>Our course is not just about passing the exam; it''s about empowering you with the tools and confidence needed to thrive in the world of Microsoft Power Platform Solution Architect. You will gain practical insights and learn from real-world scenarios, ensuring you are ready to apply your knowledge in practical situations. By the end of the course, you will have a comprehensive understanding of Microsoft Power Platform Solution Architect, and be fully prepared to take on the PL-600 exam with confidence. Enroll now and take the first step towards achieving your Microsoft Power Platform Solution Architect certification and advancing your career.</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong>&nbsp;- Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Certification -&nbsp;</strong>The participant will be able to attempt the Microsoft Power Platform Solution Architect (PL600) exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the Microsoft Power Platform Solution Architect (PL600) accreditation. This certification validates their understanding and proficiency in fundamental concepts related to Microsoft Azure, including cloud concepts, Azure services, security, privacy, compliance, and pricing. This accreditation demonstrates their ability to leverage Azure services effectively and their readiness to pursue further Azure certifications and roles</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/credentials/certifications/exams/pl-600/" title="Exam PL-600: Microsoft Power Platform Solution Architect" target="_blank">here</a></span>. We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center.&nbsp;Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>' WHERE value_id=94870;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Unleash your creativity with WSQ''s Digital Graphics Creation with Illustrator course. Our comprehensive program will guide you through the core features of Adobe Illustrator, including vector graphics creation, logo design, and typography. Designed to cater to both beginners and those looking to refine their skills, this course equips you with the essentials needed to produce professional-grade graphic designs.</p>\n<p>Structured around practical, hands-on exercises and industry-relevant projects, you''ll be enabled to apply your newfound skills in various real-world applications. Whether you aim to advance your career in graphic design or improve your skill set for personal projects, you''ll emerge from this course with a portfolio showcasing your capabilities in digital graphics creation.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Apply basic Illustrator techniques for digital graphics.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Improve Illustrator techniques through experimentation.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Evaluate and output the digital graphics.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1woteffkCeUq2wnkxYAV8Tw_XHaHzJ7DK/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Creating Professional Graphics with Adobe Illustrator Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Creating Professional Graphics with Adobe Illustrator Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guidelines of <strong>Digital Image Production RET-DNI-4003-1.1</strong> TSC under Retail Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$700.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$63.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$413.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$273.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2021003160" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2021003160" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2021003160" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2021003160) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=95831;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>This WSQ Project Management Professional (PMP) 35 PDU Training is designed for professionals seeking to enhance their project management skills and earn 35 PDUs towards PMP certification. The course focuses on scoping medium-scale projects to ensure timely completions, developing realistic project plans, and allocating resources effectively. Participants will gain expertise in implementing project methodologies, managing risks, and engaging stakeholders through structured communication.</p>\n<p>This comprehensive training covers the full project lifecycle, from planning and managing scope, budgets, and schedules to executing project deliverables and ensuring quality outcomes. Participants will also learn how to lead high-performing teams, resolve conflicts, and continuously improve processes to support organizational goals. This course is ideal for those looking to advance their careers in project management.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Scope medium-scale project requirements to drive timely completions.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Develop project plans based on realistic timelines and resource allocations</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Implement methodologies effectively to address project exigencies and derive solutions from identified root causes.</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Analyze program risks and engage stakeholders through scheduled touchpoints to discuss potential issues.</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Coordinate project deliverables against set objectives, costs, and timelines, and implement corrective actions.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1BBzxJJfTVb5vxJqNsWAOpW2V7x8Fc-Oe/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Project Management Professional (PMP) 35 PDU Training Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Project Management Professional (PMP) 35 PDU Training Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong><span lang="EN-GB">Project Management ICT-PMT-4026-1.1 TSC</span></strong><span></span><strong><span lang="EN-GB">&nbsp;</span></strong><span></span>under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Ceritification</strong> -&nbsp;The participant will be able to attempt the Project Management Professional (PMP) exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the Project Management Professional (PMP) accreditation. This certification validates their project management skills, knowledge, and experience. The PMP certification in Singapore enhances career prospects by demonstrating proficiency in project management processes and tools, globally recognized and respected within the industry.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$1,560.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$140.40</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$920.40</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$608.40</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2024045797" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2024045797" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year.&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></span></span></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2024045797" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2024045797) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=97106;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a transformative journey towards becoming a Google Professional Machine Learning Engineer. Our comprehensive preparation course is meticulously designed to cover all the critical facets of machine learning, ensuring you gain the expertise needed to pass the certification exam confidently. By engaging with this course, you will dive deep into the development of scalable machine learning models, understanding complex data pipelines, and deploying robust ML projects using Google Cloud technologies. This certification signifies to employers that you possess the acumen to leverage machine learning in a way that drives powerful, innovative solutions.</p>\n<p>This advanced training program goes beyond the fundamentals, providing insights into machine learning algorithms, model optimization, and problem-solving techniques crucial for real-world applications. You will learn how to approach machine learning engineering with an ethical and socially responsible lens while mastering the skills to build, test, and deploy AI systems that are scalable and reliable. Our curriculum is crafted to ensure that upon completion, you will not only be prepared for the Google Professional Machine Learning Engineer exam but also equipped to propel your career forward in the thriving field of AI and machine learning.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Assess and draft Google Cloud solution specifications to meet expected business machine learning requirements.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Develop implementation plans and resolve issues for Google Cloud machine learning solutions .</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Develop and review processes for metrics associated with Google Cloud mchine learning solution implementation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/144GdCxBvp9nPMQBLw18QxHUw3Q8SXSnw/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Google Professional Machine Learning Engineer Training (Synchronous e-Learning) Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Google Professional Machine Learning Engineer Training (Synchronous e-Learning) Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Cloud Computing ICT-DIT-4020-1.1&nbsp;</strong>under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Register for Google Cloud Certification</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification <span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://cloud.google.com/learn/certification?hl=en" title="Google Cloud Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;We are&nbsp; Kryterion Authorized Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$1,600.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$144.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$944.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$624.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2023040476" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023040476" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<p><span style="color: #333300;">Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</span></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=97718;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>This course introduces learners to end-to-end image generation automation using Agentic AI and n8n, combining essential image generation theory with hands-on workflow design. Participants will learn how modern AI image models work at a conceptual level, and how these models can be orchestrated, controlled, and deployed through automated pipelines.</p>\n<p>Rather than focusing on model training, the course emphasizes practical automation&mdash;showing how image generation can be treated as a repeatable, scalable process. Learners will explore how prompts, parameters, and inputs can be dynamically generated and routed using n8n, enabling automated image creation triggered by forms, webhooks, schedules, or business events.</p>\n<p>The course covers conditional and image-to-image generation workflows, explaining how controlled generation works in theory and how it can be implemented in practice using workflow logic. Participants will also learn how to design multi-step pipelines involving AI agents that plan, generate, refine, and select images, with options for both human-in-the-loop and fully autonomous systems.</p>\n<p>Finally, the course addresses quality control and deployment, including automated evaluation, filtering, error handling, and reliability considerations. By the end of the course, learners will be able to design and deploy robust, production-ready image generation workflows that integrate seamlessly into real-world applications.</p>\n<h2>Course Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Direct GAN modeling efforts across the organization</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Apply GAN computational methodologies to the problem.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Design advanced computational model with Variational Autoencoders (VAE)</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Evaluate a broad range of GAN algorithms</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Spear the application of GAN algorithms to new domains</li>\n<li>LO6:&nbsp;Establish guidelines on GAN algorithm selection</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/10nBrctvBwyLlC3FgJE2pbTp-vVzDgp-_/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Practical Image Generation Using GAN, VAE, and Diffusion Models Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Practical Image Generation Using GAN, VAE, and Diffusion Models Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of <span lang="EN-US">Computational Modelling&nbsp;<strong><span lang="EN">ICT-DIT-5001-1.1</span></strong><span></span></span>&nbsp;<strong>TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$800</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$72.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$472.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$312.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2021006714" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2021006714" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2021006714" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2021006714) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=98629;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">This course will only start from Jun 2020</span></p>\n<p>Quantum computers leverage quantum mechanical phenomena to manipulate information in a way the could drive breakthroughs beyond the scope of classical computing.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Quantum computer could spur the development of new technologies to save lives, machine leanring methods to diagnose illness sooner, materials to make more efficient devices and structues, financial strategies to live well in retirement, and algorithms to quickly direct resources such as ambulances</p>\n<p>This is a <strong>blended learning</strong> course, consisting of e-learning, webinars, online quizzes, and physical classroom training. This course explores the topics, technology and skills required to gain practice in the successful implementation of quantum computing.</p>\n<p>After the completion of the course, you will be certified as <strong>IBM Quantum Practitioner</strong> - become empowered with the knowledge and tools needed to collaboratively and individually advance the field of quantum computing and drive adoption</p>\n<h2>Journey</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Total Duration: 75 hrs</li>\n<li>25% Concepts - expanding the knowledge and understanding of the topic through lecture training, examples, videos and quizzes</li>\n<li>35% Technologies - Actual implementation of the concepts learned through simulations, hands-on labs and games</li>\n<li>40% Industry Use Cases - Realization of the real world impact of the topics covered through exposure through the exposure to industry case studies</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Brochure</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1VOF42Nv_CT1Hyx4sSF9rkWIEfOFuywDX/view?usp=sharing" title="IBM Quantum Practitioners Course Brochure" target="_blank">Download the course brochure here</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a <strong>IBM Quantum Practitioners Badge</strong> after passing the capstone project challenge and final assessment.</p>\n<p><img alt="IBM Quantum Practitioner Certification in Malaysia" src="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/media/wysiwyg/IBM_Quantum_Practitioner_Certificate.png" title="IBM Quantum Practitioner Certification in Malaysia" width="300" /></p>\n' WHERE value_id=100996;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a transformative journey with WSQ''s Digital Drawing Layout Production Using InDesign course. This course is your go-to guide for mastering the fundamentals of Adobe InDesign, from basic drawing techniques to complex layout production. By the end of the course, you''ll be adept at creating seamless designs for both print and digital platforms, tailored to your project''s specific requirements.</p>\n<p>Focused on real-world applications, our curriculum includes hands-on exercises and project-based learning. You will gain practical experience in digital drawing, typography, and layout arrangement, empowering you to excel in a multitude of design settings. Whether you''re an aspiring graphic designer or a seasoned professional looking to enhance your skill set, this course will provide you with the tools and expertise you need for success.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Establish the drawing layout requirement and create the InDesign document.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Utilize InDesign tools for drawings.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Refine drawings using InDesign.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1gGm8ytqEYAe-eHk0ZXiZfamj7T6mfpHT/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Creating Stunning Print and Digital Publications with InDesign Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Creating Stunning Print and Digital Publications with InDesign Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Manual and Digital Drawings Production RET-DNI-4004-1.1</strong> under Retail Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$350</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$31.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$206.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$136.50</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2021007827" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2021007827" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=102148;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Step up your video editing game with WSQ''s Video Editing with After Effects course. This course is structured to give you a comprehensive understanding of creating awe-inspiring visual effects, intricate animations, and professional motion graphics. Whether you are a beginner or an experienced editor, this course provides you with the expertise to breathe life into your video projects.</p>\n<p>Benefit from hands-on exercises and real-world scenarios that cover everything from the basics to more advanced techniques. You''ll explore the entire production workflow, including keyframe manipulation, 3D layers, and various visual effects. With individualized guidance and practical projects, you''ll finish the course equipped with skills that are highly sought after in the video editing and animation sectors.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Review video scripts and develop possible editing solutions using After Effects.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Develop work plan to edit the video content using After Effects and review the edited video.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Apply advanced After Effects techniques to resolve video quality issues.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Video Editing MED-MPN-4005-1.1<span lang="EN">&nbsp;</span>TSC</strong> under Media Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/18REpAi4ERHnojzKUEyJXz4RMQmDbmY2z/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Compositing and Visual Effects with After Effects Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Compositing and Visual Effects with After Effects Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$720</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$64.80</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$424.80</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$280.80</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2022014982" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2022014982" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2022014982" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2022014982) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=104752;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a comprehensive journey through the WSQ Fundamentals of the Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA) course. This course meticulously covers the latest updates from the Personal Data Protection Act 2020. Delve into practical applications of PDPA, understand how to adeptly manage data breaches in your organization, and learn the pivotal role of a Data Protection Officer. The course provides extensive training and communication strategies to ensure staff compliance with the PDPA.</p>\n<p>Demonstrating a proficient use of PDPA assessment tools is a cornerstone of this course, equipping organizations with the necessary knowledge and skills to maintain a robust data protection framework. Whether providing training for Data Protection Officers or enhancing the overall data protection culture within your organization, this course is a valuable asset for ensuring compliance and managing the complex landscape of personal data protection.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Identify legislative and regulatory requirements under the PDPA that the organisation has to comply with;</li>\n<li>Communicate key legislative and regulatory requirements under the PDPA and related management systems to relevant stakeholders to facilitate compliance;</li>\n<li>Assess the organisation&rsquo;s internal policies and procedures to ensure compliance;</li>\n<li>Identify and document areas of non-compliance in business activities;</li>\n<li>Assist in review of the organisation&rsquo;s guidelines / policies for adherence to requirements under the PDPA;</li>\n<li>Assist in the implementation of procedures to ensure adherence to requirements under the PDPA in the day-to-day operations of the organisation; and</li>\n<li>Prepare management report for follow-up action</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1e6_PhJuPwhd8ISJWWkkdZqe28z6KeNiq/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Fundamentals of the Personal Data Protection (PDPA) Act (2020) Course Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Fundamentals of the Personal Data Protection (PDPA) Act (2020) Course Brochure</a></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Data Protection Management&nbsp;ICT-CGP-3020-1.1&nbsp;</strong>TSC under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<p>Two e-certificates will be awarded to trainees who have demonstrated competency in the WSQ assessment and achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Statement of Attainment (SOA) issued by WSG. You can download the SOA from&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/public/download-cert.html" title="Downlaod SSG SOA" target="_blank">here</a></span>&nbsp;after&nbsp;3-4 weeks upon completion of the course. Note that the SOA certificate title indicates the TSC title not the course title.</li><li>Certification of Completion issued by Tertiary Infotech Pte Ltd issued after the class.</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$720</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$64.80</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$424.80</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$280.80</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover up out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://sfec.enterprisejobskills.gov.sg/Callbackhandler/Prelogin.aspx" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SkillsFuture Credit to offset course fee payable after funding. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023019520" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% cash rebate of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped at $250 per year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=105094;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Take your data analysis skills to the next level with our WSQ-accredited Text Analytics with R course. Designed to equip you with practical expertise, this course delves into essential topics such as text mining, sentiment analysis, and natural language processing. You''ll learn to use R to effectively analyze text data, recognize patterns, and make data-driven decisions. Hands-on projects and real-world examples are integrated to ensure you can apply what you''ve learned immediately.</p>\n<p>The course not only covers the fundamentals but also introduces advanced techniques to manipulate and analyze text-based data. By the end of this course, you will have the ability to apply text analytics to a range of business scenarios, thereby enhancing your role in any data-centric organization. Transform unstructured text into valuable insights and position yourself at the forefront of the data analytics field.</p>\n<h2>Course Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul></ul>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Identify and develop text analytics solutions using Cross-Industry Standard Process for Data Mining (CRISP-DM).</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Read in text corpus and perform text pre-processing using R&nbsp;</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Perform text analytics using R and modify the data with feature engineering.</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Perform sentimental analysis using R from social media data&nbsp;</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Perform sentiment summarization and visualization using R</li>\n</ul>\n<ul></ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1l9jqI0eoNmTp01BXYJZ19ojQQjji-lav/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ Text Analytics with R Course Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Text Analytics with R Course Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of <strong>Text Analytics and Processing ICT-DIT-4029-1.1</strong>&nbsp;<strong>TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$720.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$64.80</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$424.80</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$280.80</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2021010367" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2021010367" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2021010367" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2021010367) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=106968;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Immerse yourself in the world of text analytics with our WSQ-endorsed Text Analytics with Python course. This comprehensive program will cover essential techniques such as text mining, sentiment analysis, and natural language processing (NLP). Through hands-on exercises and real-world case studies, you''ll learn how to use Python to analyze and interpret large sets of text data, deriving actionable insights that can be applied across industries.</p>\n<p>By the completion of the course, you&rsquo;ll possess a robust set of skills in text analytics, capable of leveraging Python''s powerful libraries for tasks like sentiment analysis, topic modeling, and text classification. Ideal for professionals in data science, marketing, or any field requiring text analysis, this course equips you with the necessary tools to make data-informed decisions.</p>\n<h2>Course Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul></ul>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Identify and develop text analytics solutions using Cross-Industry Standard Process for Data Mining (CRISP-DM).</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Read in text corpus and perform text pre-processing using Python.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Perform text analytics and modify the data using Python with feature engineering.</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Perform sentimental analysis using Python from social media data.</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Perform sentiment summarization and visualization using Python.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of <strong>Text Analytics and Processing ICT-DIT-4029-1.1</strong>&nbsp;<strong>TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1q6z_EhGrrWR9cY5U17Nfa3Nh4BJ3PPCk/view?usp=sharing" title="Download WSQ - Python Text Mining and Analytics: Transforming Text into Insights Brochure" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Download WSQ - Python Text Mining and Analytics: Transforming Text into Insights Brochure</span></a></p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$720.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$64.80</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$424.80</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$280.80</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover up out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2022014977" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2022014977" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2022014977" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2022014977) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=107010;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Master the art of dashboard creation with our WSQ-endorsed course focused on using Excel for interactive data visualization. The course covers essential skills such as utilizing pivot tables, incorporating various data sources, and applying advanced Excel functions. With hands-on exercises and real-world examples, you''ll gain practical know-how that can be immediately applied in your work or business.</p>\n<p>Upon completing the course, you&rsquo;ll be well-equipped to build interactive dashboards that provide a dynamic and user-friendly way to interpret complex data sets. Whether you''re a business professional, data analyst, or someone interested in improving data presentation skills, this course sets the foundation for effective data visualization and decision-making through Excel dashboards.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul></ul>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Perform data analysis and create visualization using Excel</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Develop basic dashboards and scoreboards by incorporating appropriate visual elements.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Create interactive dashboard and communicate limitation of findings.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1JJH_uL_bFrLi-XrukdLweqcCgVu5rslR/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Create Interactive Dashboard Using Excel Course Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Create Interactive Dashboard Using Excel Course Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of <strong>Data Visualisation<strong><span lang="EN">&nbsp;ICT-DIT-3006-1.1</span></strong><span></span>&nbsp;TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$350</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$31.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$206.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$136.50</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2021010195" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2021010195" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=107248;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive into the world of technical drawing with this beginner-friendly WSQ course in Sketchup. Ideal for those new to 3D modeling or design, this course starts with the basics, guiding you through the Sketchup interface and fundamental drawing techniques. Master the art of creating accurate, detailed designs and models that can be applied in various engineering and architectural projects.</p>\n<p>With a focus on practical skills, this course equips you with the techniques needed for efficient drafting and 3D visualization. You''ll learn to design models, perform basic layout tasks, and understand dimensional sketching. From hobbyists to aspiring designers, this course lays the foundation for a deeper understanding and application of technical drawing. Elevate your design capabilities and get set for the next step in your career or educational journey.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul></ul>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Produce and visualize 2D/3D technical drawings using Sketchup</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Create part lists and new design using Sketchup</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Produce drawing and documentation using Sketchup</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1y6dejlcQcFa7_898IWAbNDCYVMTHmOQn/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Basic Technical Drawing with Sketchup for Beginners Course Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Basic Technical Drawing with Sketchup for Beginners Course Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of <strong><span>Technical Drawing </span></strong><strong><span lang="EN">BEV-TDR-3005-1.1-1</span></strong><span></span><strong>&nbsp;TSC</strong> under Built Environment Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$720.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$64.80</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$424.80</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$280.80</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2021010185" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2021010185" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2021010185" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2021010185) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=107535;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Unleash your creativity in video post-production with WSQ''s Video Editing with Premiere Pro course. Designed for both beginners and those looking to advance their skills, this course covers the fundamentals of editing, special effects, and sound manipulation. By the end of the course, you''ll be proficient in cutting sequences, layering transitions, and creating compelling video content that stands out.</p>\n<p>To ensure a comprehensive learning experience, this course includes hands-on exercises and real-world projects that put your skills to the test. You''ll be guided through the entire editing process, from importing and organizing media to exporting the final cut. Along the way, you''ll pick up essential skills in color correction, audio enhancement, and advanced editing techniques, providing you with a robust skill set for any video editing challenge.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul></ul>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p style="display: inline !important;">LO1: Analyze and arrange the footage in a logical sequence for editing.</p>\n</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Create editing logs and edit the shots.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Resolve audio and still issues.</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Collaborate with production teams to edit clip and color.</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Perform final touch up to clean up imperfections.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1R0NkKgO4KL-bAbI6TwyAvVFGaUkevo8A/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Video Editing with Premiere Pro Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Video Editing with Premiere Pro Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of <strong><span lang="EN">Video Editing </span></strong><strong><span lang="EN">MED-MPN-3005-1.1&nbsp;</span></strong><span></span><strong>TSC</strong> under Media Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$720</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$64.80</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$424.80</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$280.80</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2022014976" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2022014976" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2022014976" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2022014976) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=107593;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Elevate your financial analysis capabilities with our specialized WSQ-endorsed course on Python Programming for Finance. This comprehensive course delves into the application of Python for various financial tasks including trading algorithms, portfolio management, and risk assessment. Through hands-on exercises and real-world financial case studies, you will learn how to utilize Python''s powerful libraries to analyze financial data, forecast trends, and make data-driven decisions.</p>\n<p>Upon completing the course, you&rsquo;ll have a robust skill set in applying Python for financial analysis and strategy development. Whether you''re a financial analyst, a portfolio manager, or someone keen on fintech, this course equips you with the computational tools and knowledge to optimize your financial operations and strategies effectively.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Apply Python programming to meet business requirements.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Code data types and operators.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Organize codes using conditional and loop for problem-solving.</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Code Python functions and scripts for business use cases.</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Code import and prepare finance data using Python Pandas package.</li>\n<li>LO6:&nbsp;Test Python codes with aggregation and visualization.</li>\n<li>LO7:&nbsp;Improve and document Python codes to analyse finance data.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of <strong>Programming and Coding ACC-DIT-3018-1.1<span lang="EN">&nbsp;</span>TSC</strong> under Accountancy Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1aNIi0aXIT1cbcgzcq16ikBisQ-XFh2ow/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Python Programming for Finance Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Python Programming for Finance Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$1000</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$90.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$590.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$390.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover up out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2022014980" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2022014980" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2022014980" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2022014980) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=110872;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p><span>Unlock the power of Excel in the domain of trading and investment with this comprehensive training. Delve into foundational and advanced strategies including the Moving Average Crossover, Volume Weight Average Pricing (VWAP), and the Relative Strength Indicator (RSI). Complement these with a deep understanding of key metrics like Expected Return, Beta, and Volatility, setting the stage for informed and data-driven financial decisions. <br /><br />Furthermore, this course illuminates the intricacies of the Capital Asset Pricing Model, a cornerstone in modern financial theory. Whether you''re a budding trader or an investment professional, the integration of Excel with these critical strategies ensures a robust approach to the financial markets, optimizing your potential for success.</span></p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=111427;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p><span>Unlock the power of Excel in the domain of trading and investment with this comprehensive training. Delve into foundational and advanced strategies including the Moving Average Crossover, Volume Weight Average Pricing (VWAP), and the Relative Strength Indicator (RSI). Complement these with a deep understanding of key metrics like Expected Return, Beta, and Volatility, setting the stage for informed and data-driven financial decisions. <br /><br />Furthermore, this course illuminates the intricacies of the Capital Asset Pricing Model, a cornerstone in modern financial theory. Whether you''re a budding trader or an investment professional, the integration of Excel with these critical strategies ensures a robust approach to the financial markets, optimizing your potential for success.</span></p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>' WHERE value_id=111458;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Blockchain is essentially a decentralised and distributed database peer-to-peer technology (Web3) that was popularised by the Bitcoin global cryptocurrency platform since 2009. There has been a lot of hype around Blockchain and Web3 technology in recent times. Almost all Fin-Tech heavy weights are pouring investments into various Blockchain projects such as DeFi, GameFi, Metaverse, NFT etc .Governments and regulators are also equally interested in this disruptive technology.</p>\n\n<p>The potential applications for Blockchains and Bitcoin-like cryptocurrencies are enormous.&nbsp;This course will teach you the fundamentals on Crypto,, NFT, Metaverse, DeFi, GameFi. It also covers the Crypto Security and how you can protect your Crypto from hacking and fraud.</p>\n\n\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n\n\n' WHERE value_id=112269;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p><span style="color: #ff0000;">This course is not yet approved for WSQ funding</span></p>\n\n<p>Embark on a comprehensive journey through the WSQ Fundamentals of the Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA) course. This course meticulously covers the latest updates from the Personal Data Protection Act 2020. Delve into practical applications of PDPA, understand how to adeptly manage data breaches in your organization, and learn the pivotal role of a Data Protection Officer. The course provides extensive training and communication strategies to ensure staff compliance with the PDPA.</p>\n<p>Demonstrating a proficient use of PDPA assessment tools is a cornerstone of this course, equipping organizations with the necessary knowledge and skills to maintain a robust data protection framework. Whether providing training for Data Protection Officers or enhancing the overall data protection culture within your organization, this course is a valuable asset for ensuring compliance and managing the complex landscape of personal data protection.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By the end of the course, learners will be able to&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Identify legislative and regulatory requirements under the PDPA that the organisation has to comply with;</li>\n<li>Communicate key legislative and regulatory requirements under the PDPA and related management systems to relevant stakeholders to facilitate compliance;</li>\n<li>Assess the organisation&rsquo;s internal policies and procedures to ensure compliance;</li>\n<li>Identify and document areas of non-compliance in business activities;</li>\n<li>Assist in review of the organisation&rsquo;s guidelines / policies for adherence to requirements under the PDPA;</li>\n<li>Assist in the implementation of procedures to ensure adherence to requirements under the PDPA in the day-to-day operations of the organisation; and</li>\n<li>Prepare management report for follow-up action</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1e6_PhJuPwhd8ISJWWkkdZqe28z6KeNiq/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Fundamentals of the Personal Data Protection (PDPA) Act (2020) Course Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Fundamentals of the Personal Data Protection (PDPA) Act (2020) Course Brochure</a></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Data Protection Management&nbsp;ICT-CGP-3020-1.1&nbsp;</strong>TSC under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n\n<div style=" width: 80%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=113370;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a journey to master the Fundamentals of<strong> ISO 9001 Quality Management System</strong> (QMS) with our comprehensive course. Designed for professionals seeking to enhance their understanding of quality management principles, this course will guide you through the key elements of the ISO 9001 standard, enabling you to implement and maintain a robust QMS within your organization.</p>\n<p>Explore the core components of ISO 9001, including process approach, risk-based thinking, and continuous improvement. Gain insights into quality management best practices, learn to identify gaps, and develop strategies to ensure customer satisfaction and operational excellence. With up to 70% WSQ funding subsidy available, equip yourself with the knowledge and skills necessary to create a culture of quality and improve your organization''s performance. Enroll today and kick-start your ISO 9001 journey.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Identify area of improvement using ISO 9001 QMS and perform process improvement.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Apply quality tools from QMS and monitor key metrics.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Evaluate and assess compliance against QMS requirements.</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Follow up on the QMS improvement process sand document continual improvement.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1gIh4leF7_r1fkGsOXu8cXskRLRSYavNA/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Fundamentals of ISO 9001 Quality Management SystemI Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Fundamentals of ISO 9001 Quality Management System Course Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Quality System Management PPRE-QUA-4007-1.1&nbsp;</strong><strong>TSC</strong> under Precision Engineering Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$800</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$72.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$472.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$312.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2023020563" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023020563" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023020563" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2023020563) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=123243;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Elevate your financial management skills with our Advanced Transactional Accounting with Xero course, specially designed for professionals seeking to expand their accounting proficiency. This comprehensive program will guide you through the powerful features of Xero''s software, enabling you to streamline your accounting processes, automate transactions, and analyze financial data effectively.</p>\n<p>Delve into advanced topics such as complex invoicing, budgeting, multicurrency transactions, and financial reporting, with hands-on exercises and real-world examples. Plus, take advantage of up to 70% WSQ funding subsidy to further your education. Enroll today and unlock your full potential in transactional accounting with Xero, while enjoying significant savings.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Prepare for transactional accounting and double-entry accounting.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Produce accurate financial statements and report with Xero.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Determine the impact of accounting standards on financial information.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/14C_kWY6lAssg5rbK1XNaK9oL0169PT3g/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Advanced Transactional Accounting with Xero Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Advanced Transactional Accounting with Xero Course Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Transactional Accounting&nbsp;ACC-CRP-4009-1.1&nbsp;TSC</strong> under Accounting Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$800</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$72.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$472.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$312.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2023020565" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023020565" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023020565" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2023020565) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=123641;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Mastering the basics in AI can help you jump-start your career and get ready to dive deeper into the other technical opportunities Azure offers. Artificial intelligence (AI) opens doors into possibilities that might have seemed like science fiction only yesterday. Using AI, you can build solutions, improve your apps and advance technology in many fields, including healthcare, financial management, and environmental protection, to name just a few.</p>\n<p>This course completely covers the AI-900 exam from start to finish.&nbsp;The Azure AI Fundamental AI-900 exam covers the following topics:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Describe AI workloads and considerations (15-20%)</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Describe fundamental principles of machine learning on Azure (30-35%)</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Describe features of computer vision workloads on Azure (15-20%)</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Describe features of Natural Language Processing (NLP) workloads on Azure (15-20%)</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Describe features of conversational AI workloads on Azure (15-20%)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This course goes over each requirement of the exam in detail and prepare you for the AI-900 exam.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Implement AI applications with Microsoft Azure services.</li>\n<li>Deploy AI workflows on Azure.</li>\n<li>Identify and report any issues with AI anomaly detector.</li>\n<li>Maintain data interoperability and perform data cleaning with Azure knowledge mining.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1RDqcDDGmvQkTVLCZBuYGE-3OwS_9G_I0/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Microsoft Azure AI Fundamentals (AI-900) Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ&nbsp;- Microsoft Azure AI Fundamentals (AI-900) Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong><span lang="EN">Artificial Intelligence Application in Product Development </span></strong><strong><span lang="EN">ICT-TEM-3034-1.1</span></strong><span></span><strong>&nbsp;TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Certification -&nbsp;</strong>The participant will be able to attempt the Microsoft Azure AI Fundamentals (AI900) exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the&nbsp;Microsoft Azure AI Fundamentals (AI900) accreditation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Microsoft Learning Partner</h2>\n<p>We are <strong>Authorised&nbsp;Microsoft Learning Partner (Org ID:&nbsp; 5238476).</strong> To get the official Microsoft certification, please register your certification exam at Pearson Vue Test Center.</p>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>We are <strong>Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center</strong>. Once you have prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification<span style="text-decoration: underline;"> <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/credentials/certifications/azure-ai-fundamentals/?practice-assessment-type=certification" title="AZ-900" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;The course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n<p>You can purchase the exam voucher (one of the lowest prices in Singapore) at<span style="text-decoration: underline;">&nbsp;</span><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/microsoft-fundamental-certification-exam-vouchers.html" title="Microsoft Fundamental Certification Exam Voucher" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Microsoft Fundamental Certification Exam Voucher</span>.</a></p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$800</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$72.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$472.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$312.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2023021100" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023021100" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023021100" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2023021100) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=123870;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Learn to unlock business potential through effective negotiation strategies in this WSQ-accredited course. Participants will develop the ability to identify negotiation outcomes, understand the context of negotiation, and prepare detailed background information to set a strong foundation. Gain insights into negotiation styles, with considerations for social and cultural nuances, and master planning techniques to lead successful discussions.</p>\n<p>This course also covers practical negotiation tactics, including opening offers, handling difficult personalities, and employing anchoring and framing techniques for mutual benefits. Participants will practice listening, building empathy, avoiding common pitfalls like using round numbers, and leveraging precedents for favorable outcomes. Closing offers, debriefing, and evaluating negotiation results will ensure participants leave equipped to excel in professional negotiations.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Identify negotiation outcomes, context of negotiation and prepare relevant background information for negotiation.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Apply negotiation techniques during negotiation and record negotiations for evaluation after negotiation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1t2HCj9SKgz_vUmaZnXcoE_dXh3rpbjR8/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Unlocking Business Potential with Strategic Negotiation Tactics Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Unlocking Business Potential with Strategic Negotiation Tactics Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Business Negotiation ICT-BIN-3105-1&nbsp;TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$750</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$67.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$442.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$292.50</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2023020567" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023020567" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023020567" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2023020567) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the P<a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">SEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=124019;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>AutoCAD Mechanical is a powerful computer-aided design (CAD) software tool used primarily in the mechanical engineering industry. It provides specialized tools and features to create and edit 2D drawings and 3D models of mechanical parts and assemblies. AutoCAD Mechanical includes libraries of pre-drawn parts and symbols, as well as automated routines for generating bills of materials and creating detailed manufacturing documentation. The software is designed to help mechanical engineers and designers streamline their workflow, reduce errors and increase efficiency. AutoCAD Mechanical is part of the larger AutoCAD family of software products and is known for its precision and accuracy, making it a popular tool for professionals in the engineering, manufacturing, and construction industries.</p>\n<p>This course is designed to teach individuals how to create detailed and precise technical drawings using AutoCAD Mechanical software.&nbsp;This course will cover the basic features of the software, including how to create and modify geometry, add dimensions and annotations, create blocks and symbols, and generate bill of materials.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Formulate solutions for technical drawing problems using AutoCAD Mechanical toolset to devise metrics and guidelines.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Review and analyze technical drawings to deliver design solutions.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Review technical drawings to ensure conformance to specifications and standards.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1YItQNGIJ8Otg_eg31BB2uqaRLQLCvMDy/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Technical Drawing with AutoCAD Mechanical Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Technical Drawing with AutoCAD Mechanical Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Technical Drawing DSN-TDR-4005-1.1&nbsp;</strong>under Design Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1RUMXigsDyI_u4lWVGB2hjtgr3xsuYZbz/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Technical Drawing with AutoCAD Course Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Technical Drawing with AutoCAD Course Brochure</a></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of <strong>Technical Drawing DSN-TDR-3005-1.11</strong> TSC under Design Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong>&nbsp;- Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapor</strong>e - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Autodesk ATC</h2>\n<p>We are&nbsp;<strong>Autodesk Authorized Training Center</strong>. To get the official certification, please register on Pearson Vue Test CenterTo get the official certification, please register on Pearson Vue Test Center</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$900</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$81.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$531.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$351.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2023037469" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023037469" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023037469" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2023037469) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=125301;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a transformative journey of technical prowess with our Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA) Exam Prep course. This meticulously designed course aims at equipping learners with the requisite knowledge and practical skills essential for mastering Kubernetes orchestration. Delving into the core functionalities and advanced features of Kubernetes, this course lays a solid foundation for managing and scaling containerized applications with ease and precision. The comprehensive curriculum encapsulates the essential Kubernetes concepts, security best practices, networking policies, and various other pivotal aspects, aligning with the course highlights to provide a well-rounded learning experience.</p>\n<p>Transitioning to the realms of professional expertise, this course facilitates a thorough understanding of Kubernetes orchestration, empowering learners to manage complex Kubernetes clusters proficiently. Through a blend of theoretical insights and hands-on exercises, learners will gain a profound understanding of deploying, managing, and scaling applications in a Kubernetes environment. Additionally, the course prepares learners for the Certified Kubernetes Administrator exam, providing them with the confidence and knowledge required to excel. The rigorous training and practical exposure provided through this course are instrumental in not only preparing learners for the CKA exam but also in fostering a robust understanding of Kubernetes orchestration, thus paving the way for a successful and fulfilling career in the burgeoning field of container orchestration and Kubernetes administration.</p>\n\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.isaca.org/credentialing/cisa title="CISACertification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n\n\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://training.linuxfoundation.org/certification-catalog/" title="Linux Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n<p>For WSQ funding, please checkout the details at&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/wsq-certified-kubernetes-administrator-cka-exam-prep-synchronous-e-learning.html" title="WSQ - Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA) Training (Synchronous e-Learning)">WSQ - Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA) Training (Synchronous e-Learning)</a></span><span style="text-decoration: underline;"></span></p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=125630;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a transformative journey of technical prowess with our Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA) Exam Prep course. This meticulously designed course aims at equipping learners with the requisite knowledge and practical skills essential for mastering Kubernetes orchestration. Delving into the core functionalities and advanced features of Kubernetes, this course lays a solid foundation for managing and scaling containerized applications with ease and precision. The comprehensive curriculum encapsulates the essential Kubernetes concepts, security best practices, networking policies, and various other pivotal aspects, aligning with the course highlights to provide a well-rounded learning experience.</p>\n<p>Transitioning to the realms of professional expertise, this course facilitates a thorough understanding of Kubernetes orchestration, empowering learners to manage complex Kubernetes clusters proficiently. Through a blend of theoretical insights and hands-on exercises, learners will gain a profound understanding of deploying, managing, and scaling applications in a Kubernetes environment. Additionally, the course prepares learners for the Certified Kubernetes Administrator exam, providing them with the confidence and knowledge required to excel. The rigorous training and practical exposure provided through this course are instrumental in not only preparing learners for the CKA exam but also in fostering a robust understanding of Kubernetes orchestration, thus paving the way for a successful and fulfilling career in the burgeoning field of container orchestration and Kubernetes administration.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://training.linuxfoundation.org/certification-catalog/" title="Linux Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>' WHERE value_id=125672;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Master the essentials of game development with a focus on Unity and C# programming. This course introduces learners to key C# methodologies for software design and development in Unity. Participants will explore core concepts like scripting fundamentals, object-oriented programming, and the integration of controls and functionalities required to meet game design specifications. By the end of the course, learners will be able to identify and apply essential C# methods to create functional Unity game software.</p>\n<p>The course also emphasizes practical application, enabling learners to design and build interactive games using C# classes and objects. Learners will gain hands-on experience with Unity''s software functionalities, including version control and documentation best practices. This comprehensive approach equips participants with the skills to evaluate, create, and maintain Unity game projects aligned with industry standards.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Determine basic software components using C# methodologies to meet Unity game functional specifications.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Apply C# methodologies for Unity game software creation.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Identify C# controls and functionalities to meet Unity game software design requirements.</li>\n<li>LO4:&nbsp;Evaluate C# object oriented programming methodology for Unity software design</li>\n<li>LO5:&nbsp;Produce C# design documentation with version control to meet user specifications.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1HyBuAnrE5BGwYYK7MrUqKKjmLDsk1S24/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Mastering Game Development with Unity and C# Programming Basics Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Mastering Game Development with Unity and C# Programming Basics Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Software Design ICT-DES-3005-1.1&nbsp;</strong>under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://home.pearsonvue.com/unity/" title="Unity Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>. We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$800</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$72.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$472.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$312.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2024042310" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2024042310" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year.&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><span style="color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></span></span><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;"><br /></span></p>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=125748;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>The DP-300 Azure Database Administrator Associate course is meticulously designed to elevate your skills and understanding of Azure SQL Database and SQL Server in Azure virtual machines. This course will guide you through the intricacies of designing Azure SQL Database for cloud-native applications, exploring Azure SQL Database Managed Instance, and understanding Microsoft Intelligent Data Platform roles.</p>\n<p>With a comprehensive curriculum that covers both theoretical and practical aspects of Azure database administration, you will gain the knowledge and confidence needed to excel in your career. Our expert instructors, coupled with hands-on exercises and real-world examples, will ensure that you leave with a strong grasp of the course material and the ability to apply it in practical situations.</p>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/credentials/certifications/exams/dp-300/" title="Exam DP-300: Administering Microsoft Azure SQL Solutions" target="_blank">here</a></span>. We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center.&nbsp;Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong>&nbsp;- Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Certification -&nbsp;</strong>The participant will be able to attempt the Azure Database Administrator Associate (DP300) exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the&nbsp;Azure Database Administrator Associate (DP300)&nbsp;accreditation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Microsoft Learning Partner</h2>\n<p>We are <strong>Authorised&nbsp;Microsoft Learning Partner (Org ID:&nbsp; 5238476).</strong> To get the official Microsoft certification, please register your certification exam at Pearson Vue Test Center.</p>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>We are <strong>Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center</strong>. Once you have prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification<span style="text-decoration: underline;"> <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/credentials/certifications/azure-database-administrator-associate/?practice-assessment-type=certification" title="DP-300" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;The course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n<p>You can purchase the exam voucher (one of the lowest prices in Singapore) at<span style="text-decoration: underline;">&nbsp;</span><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.my/microsoft-role-based-certification-exam-vouchers-malaysia.html" title="Microsoft Role-Based Certification Exam Voucher" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Microsoft Role-Based Certification Exam Voucher</span></a>.</p>\n<div style=" width: 80%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course.</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=125765;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<div>\n<div>The Microsoft Azure Administrator exam focuses on common tasks and concepts that an administrator needs to understand to deploy and manage infrastructure in Microsoft Azure. This course focuses on skills and knowledge needed to manage Azure subscriptions; analyze resource utilization and consumption; manage resource groups; establish storage accounts; import/export data; configure Azure files; implement backup; create, configure, and automate VM deployment; manage VMs and VM backups; implement, manage, and connect virtual networks; create and configure Network Security Groups; manage Azure AD and its objects; and implement and manage hybrid identities. Passing the Microsoft Azure Administrator exam earns your Microsoft Certified: Azure Administrator Associate certification, demonstrating your skills in implementing, monitoring, and maintaining Microsoft Azure solutions, including major services related to compute, storage, network, and security.<br /><br />The goal of this course is to provide you with all the tools you need to prepare for the AZ-104: Microsoft Azure Administrator exam &mdash; including text explanations, video demos, lab activities, self-assessment questions, and a practice exam&mdash;to increase your chances of passing the exam on your first try.<br /><br /><strong>Course contains:</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>CertPREP lessons</li>\n<li>Practice test with Practice and Certification modes</li>\n<li>Lab suit</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong>&nbsp;- Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Certification -&nbsp;</strong>The participant will be able to attempt the Azure Network Engineer Associate Exam Prep (AZ700) exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the&nbsp;Azure Network Engineer Associate Exam Prep (AZ700) accreditation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Microsoft Learning Partner</h2>\n<p>We are&nbsp;<strong>Authorised&nbsp;Microsoft Learning Partner (Org ID:&nbsp; 5238476).</strong>&nbsp;To get the official Microsoft certification, please register your certification exam at Pearson Vue Test Center.</p>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>We are <strong>Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center</strong>. Once you have prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification<span style="text-decoration: underline;"> <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/credentials/certifications/azure-network-engineer-associate/?practice-assessment-type=certification" title="AZ-700" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;The course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n<p>You can purchase the exam voucher (one of the lowest prices in Singapore) at<span style="text-decoration: underline;">&nbsp;</span><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.sg/microsoft-role-based-certification-exam-vouchers.html" title="Microsoft Role-Based Certification Exam Voucher" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Microsoft Role-Based Certification Exam Voucher</span></a>.</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=125917;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a journey to master the world of Microsoft 365 with our MS-900 Microsoft 365 Fundamentals Exam Prep course. This comprehensive training is meticulously designed to provide you with the essential knowledge and skills needed to excel in the MS-900 certification exam, setting you apart in the competitive field of cloud services and office solutions. Our expert instructors will guide you through the intricacies of Microsoft 365, ensuring that you are well-prepared to tackle the exam with confidence.</p>\n<p>Our course is structured to offer you a hands-on learning experience, allowing you to apply the concepts learned in real-world scenarios. You will gain a deep understanding of Microsoft 365 services, including Office 365, Windows 10, and Enterprise Mobility + Security, and how to leverage them to create efficient and scalable solutions for businesses and organizations. By the end of the course, you will be fully equipped to take on the MS-900 certification exam and take your career to new heights. Enroll now and unlock the power of Microsoft 365.</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong>&nbsp;- Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Certification -&nbsp;</strong>The participant will be able to attempt the Microsoft 365 Fundamentals (MS900) exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the&nbsp;Microsoft 365 Fundamentals (MS900) accreditation. This certification validates their understanding and proficiency in fundamental concepts related to Microsoft Azure, including cloud concepts, Azure services, security, privacy, compliance, and pricing. This accreditation demonstrates their ability to leverage Azure services effectively and their readiness to pursue further Azure certifications and roles</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/credentials/certifications/exams/ms-900/" title="Exam MS-900: Microsoft 365 Fundamentals" target="_blank">here</a></span>. We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center.&nbsp;Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>' WHERE value_id=126029;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<div>\n<div>The Microsoft Azure Administrator exam focuses on common tasks and concepts that an administrator needs to understand to deploy and manage infrastructure in Microsoft Azure. This course focuses on skills and knowledge needed to manage Azure subscriptions; analyze resource utilization and consumption; manage resource groups; establish storage accounts; import/export data; configure Azure files; implement backup; create, configure, and automate VM deployment; manage VMs and VM backups; implement, manage, and connect virtual networks; create and configure Network Security Groups; manage Azure AD and its objects; and implement and manage hybrid identities. Passing the Microsoft Azure Administrator exam earns your Microsoft Certified: Azure Administrator Associate certification, demonstrating your skills in implementing, monitoring, and maintaining Microsoft Azure solutions, including major services related to compute, storage, network, and security.<br /><br />The goal of this course is to provide you with all the tools you need to prepare for the AZ-104: Microsoft Azure Administrator exam &mdash; including text explanations, video demos, lab activities, self-assessment questions, and a practice exam&mdash;to increase your chances of passing the exam on your first try.<br /><br /><strong>Course contains:</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>CertPREP lessons</li>\n<li>Practice test with Practice and Certification modes</li>\n<li>Lab suit</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong>&nbsp;- Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Certification -&nbsp;</strong>The participant will be able to attempt the Azure Network Engineer Associate Exam Prep (AZ700) exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the&nbsp;Azure Network Engineer Associate Exam Prep (AZ700) accreditation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Microsoft Learning Partner</h2>\n<p>We are <strong>Authorised&nbsp;Microsoft Learning Partner (Org ID:&nbsp; 5238476).</strong> To get the official Microsoft certification, please register your certification exam at Pearson Vue Test Center.</p>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>We are <strong>Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center</strong>. Once you have prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification<span style="text-decoration: underline;"> <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/credentials/certifications/azure-network-engineer-associate/?practice-assessment-type=certification" title="AZ-700" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;The course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n<p>You can purchase the exam voucher (one of the lowest prices in Singapore) at<span style="text-decoration: underline;">&nbsp;</span><a href="AZ-700%20Azure%20Network%20Engineer%20Associate%20Exam%20Prep" title="Microsoft Role-Based Certification Exam Voucher" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Microsoft Role-Based Certification Exam Voucher</span></a>.</p>' WHERE value_id=126045;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>AutoCAD Electrical is a software program used for the creation and modification of electrical control systems and schematics. It is a specialized version of the AutoCAD software and provides an extensive library of electrical symbols, components, and circuitry. With AutoCAD Electrical, engineers and designers can create precise, detailed electrical schematics, panel layouts, and other control system designs.</p>\n<p>This course aims to equip students with the knowledge and skills necessary for the production of technical drawings using AutoCAD Electrical software. It covers topics such as drafting standards and conventions, problem-solving techniques, and quality control measures. Upon completion of the course, students will be able to create, modify, and review technical drawings while adhering to relevant standards and specifications.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Formulate solutions for technical drawing problems using AutoCAD Electrical to devise metrics and guidelines.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Review and analyze technical drawings to deliver design solutions.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Review technical drawings to ensure conformance to specifications and standards.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1u5gszGj-g7HLYaudUTLL1YjnmuuhoQCL/view?usp=drive_link" title="WSQ - Technical Drawing with AutoCAD Electrical Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Technical Drawing with AutoCAD Electrical Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Technical Drawing DSN-TDR-4005-1.1&nbsp;</strong>under Design Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1_nGpWRKVJrbREd8weE79wVY3l7BFZSoj/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Technical Drawing with AutoCAD Course Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Technical Drawing with AutoCAD Course Brochure</a></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of <strong>Technical Drawing DSN-TDR-3005-1.11</strong> TSC under Design Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong>&nbsp;- Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapor</strong>e - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Autodesk ATC</h2>\n<p>We are&nbsp;<strong>Autodesk Authorized Training Center</strong>. To get the official certification, please register on Pearson Vue Test CenterTo get the official certification, please register on Pearson Vue Test Center</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$900</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$81.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$531.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$351.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2023037466" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023037466" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\n<p><span>To check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023037466" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2023037466) </span></a></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=127782;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>WSQ Automate Creative Video Editing with Agentic AI Workflows and n8n equips media professionals and content creators with future-ready skills in AI-powered video editing. Learn how to develop effective editing strategies and structured workflows that align with creative goals. Using n8n and Agentic AI, participants will build dynamic video editing pipelines that automate routine tasks and enhance the quality and consistency of video content.</p>\n<p>Participants will also gain skills in assessing footage for storytelling impact and compliance, automating review and approval processes, and integrating new AI technologies to maintain industry standards. This course empowers learners to take remedial action using advanced tools while future-proofing their editing capabilities with the latest in AI-driven automation.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Develop editing strategies and work plans to achieve creative vision.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Assess edited footage to enhance storytelling and ensure technical compliance.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Develop remedial actions to ensure industry compliance and facilitate the adoption of new technologies in visual editing.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1FAdxXIw75FNqaI1uI4TjVdLjkODOSjib/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Turning Raw Footage into Fabulous Videos with iMovie Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ -&nbsp;<span data-sheets-root="1">Automate Creative Video Editing with Agentic AI Workflows and n8n</span></a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong><span lang="EN">Video Editing&nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span lang="EN">MED-MPN-4005-1.1</span></strong><span></span><strong>&nbsp;</strong>under Media Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapor</strong>e - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$750.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$67.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$442.50</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$292.50</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2023036088" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023036088" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023036088" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2023036088) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=128452;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Looking to enhance your data analysis skills? Enroll in our Neo4j Professional Graph Database Course and delve into the world of graph database management. This comprehensive course equips you with the knowledge and expertise to harness the power of Neo4j, a leading graph database technology. Through interactive sessions and hands-on exercises, you''ll learn advanced techniques to model, store, and query complex data relationships effectively. Gain valuable insights from real-world case studies and explore practical applications of graph databases across various industries.</p>\n<p>Whether you''re a data analyst, database administrator, or aspiring data professional, this course is designed to boost your career prospects in the rapidly evolving field of data analysis. Don''t miss out on this opportunity to upskill and unlock new possibilities in your professional journey. Enjoy up to 70% WSQ funding subsidy.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Perform installation, configuration and maintaining of Neo4j databases.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Troubleshoot database errors and user access issues on Neo4j databases.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Analyse performance statistics and implement regular data backup on Neo4j databases.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1esDkE3m4joCS5lKU-uiUdmMoh0gnOG0Y/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Neo4j Professional Graph Database Course Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Neo4j Professional Graph Database Course Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong><span>Database Administration </span></strong><strong><span>ICT-OUS-3006-1.1</span></strong><span></span><strong>&nbsp;TSC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Certification Exam</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://graphacademy.neo4j.com/courses/neo4j-certification/" title="Neo4j Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$800</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$72.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$472.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$312.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2023036640" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023036640" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023036640" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2023036640) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a>and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=129845;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Enhance your expertise in Sustainability Reporting and GRI (Global Reporting Initiative) Standards with our comprehensive course. This program is designed to equip professionals with the necessary skills and knowledge to develop sustainability reports that meet international standards. Learn how to assess environmental impacts, make informed decisions, and drive sustainable initiatives in your organization.</p>\n<p>The course provides in-depth insights into GRI Standards, the world''s most widely used sustainability reporting guidelines. Participants will gain practical experience in utilizing these guidelines to enhance their company''s social responsibility profile and improve overall business performance. Our course empowers you to align your business strategy with sustainable development goals, thereby creating a positive impact on your company and society.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Identify objectives of sustainability reports in accordance with organisational procedures.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Structure and collaborate with stakeholders on sustainability reportig based on GRI standards.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Proofread and submit sustainability reports with data displayed effectively to relevant stakeholders.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/18g45XjDaGpAQC8d7rCoRTcd9ggd-PbjL/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Sustainability Reporting and GRI Standards Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Sustainability Reporting and GRI Standards Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong>Technical Report Writing EPW-BIN-3043-1.1<span lang="EN"></span><span><strong>&nbsp;</strong>T</span></strong><span></span><strong></strong><strong>SC</strong> under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapore</strong> - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$900</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$81.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$531.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$351.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2023036644" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023036644" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023036644" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2023036644) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=130551;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<div><span>The Microsoft Azure Security Technologies course focuses on the knowledge needed to manage Azure Active Directory identities; configure secure access with Azure AD; manage application access and access control; implement advanced network security; configure advanced security for compute; monitor security with Azure Monitor, Azure Firewall manager, Azure Security Center, Azure Defender, and Azure Sentinel; configure security policies; configure security for storage and databases; and configure and manage Key Vault. You will also learn to demonstrate your real-world knowledge of Microsoft Azure security, including tools and techniques for protecting identity, access, platforms, data, and applications, and for effectively managing security operations.</span><br /><br /><span>The goal of this course is to provide you with all the tools you need to prepare for the AZ-500: Microsoft Azure Security Technologies exam &mdash; including text explanations, video demos, lab activities, self-assessment questions, and a practice exam&mdash; to increase your chances of passing the exam on your first try.</span><strong>Required course materials:</strong><span>&nbsp;Pearson CertPREP Exam Ref AZ-500 Microsoft Azure Security Technologies</span></div>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong>&nbsp;- Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Certification -&nbsp;</strong>The participant will be able to attempt the Azure Solutions Architct Expert (AZ305) exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the Azure Solutions Architct Expert (AZ305)accreditation. This certification validates their understanding and proficiency in fundamental concepts related to Microsoft Azure, including cloud concepts, Azure services, security, privacy, compliance, and pricing. This accreditation demonstrates their ability to leverage Azure services effectively and their readiness to pursue further Azure certifications and roles</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Microsoft Learning Partner</h2>\n<p>We are <strong>Authorised&nbsp;Microsoft Learning Partner (Org ID:&nbsp; 5238476).</strong> To get the official Microsoft certification, please register your certification exam at Pearson Vue Test Center.</p>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>We are <strong>Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center</strong>. Once you have prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification<span style="text-decoration: underline;"> <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/credentials/certifications/exams/az-305/" title="AZ-305" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;The course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n<p>You can purchase the exam voucher (one of the lowest prices in Singapore) at<span style="text-decoration: underline;">&nbsp;</span><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.my/microsoft-role-based-certification-exam-vouchers-malaysia.html" title="Microsoft Role-Based Certification Exam Voucher" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Microsoft Role-Based Certification Exam Voucher</span></a>.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="http://www.hrdf.com.my/wps/portal/PSMB/MainEN/Schemes/HRDF/" title="HRDF claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRDF SBL Claimable for Employers Registered with HRDF</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="84" src="media/wysiwyg/14054931_1763340620617768_4715474791535353517_n.jpg" title="HRDF claimable" width="64" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136109;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<div>\n<div>The Microsoft Azure Administrator exam focuses on common tasks and concepts that an administrator needs to understand to deploy and manage infrastructure in Microsoft Azure. This course focuses on skills and knowledge needed to manage Azure subscriptions; analyze resource utilization and consumption; manage resource groups; establish storage accounts; import/export data; configure Azure files; implement backup; create, configure, and automate VM deployment; manage VMs and VM backups; implement, manage, and connect virtual networks; create and configure Network Security Groups; manage Azure AD and its objects; and implement and manage hybrid identities. Passing the Microsoft Azure Administrator exam earns your Microsoft Certified: Azure Administrator Associate certification, demonstrating your skills in implementing, monitoring, and maintaining Microsoft Azure solutions, including major services related to compute, storage, network, and security.<br /><br />The goal of this course is to provide you with all the tools you need to prepare for the AZ-104: Microsoft Azure Administrator exam &mdash; including text explanations, video demos, lab activities, self-assessment questions, and a practice exam&mdash;to increase your chances of passing the exam on your first try.<br /><br /><strong>Course contains:</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>CertPREP lessons</li>\n<li>Practice test with Practice and Certification modes</li>\n<li>Lab suit</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong>&nbsp;- Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Certification -&nbsp;</strong>The participant will be able to attempt the Azure Network Engineer Associate Exam Prep (AZ700) exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the&nbsp;Azure Network Engineer Associate Exam Prep (AZ700) accreditation.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Microsoft Learning Partner</h2>\n<p>We are <strong>Authorised&nbsp;Microsoft Learning Partner (Org ID:&nbsp; 5238476).</strong> To get the official Microsoft certification, please register your certification exam at Pearson Vue Test Center.</p>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>We are <strong>Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center</strong>. Once you have prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification<span style="text-decoration: underline;"> <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/credentials/certifications/azure-network-engineer-associate/?practice-assessment-type=certification" title="AZ-700" target="_blank">here</a></span>.&nbsp;The course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n<p>You can purchase the exam voucher (one of the lowest prices in Singapore) at<span style="text-decoration: underline;">&nbsp;</span><a href="https://www.tertiarycourses.com.my/microsoft-role-based-certification-exam-vouchers-malaysia.html" title="Microsoft Role-Based Certification Exam Voucher" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Microsoft Role-Based Certification Exam Voucher</span></a>.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="http://www.hrdf.com.my/wps/portal/PSMB/MainEN/Schemes/HRDF/" title="HRDF claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRDF SBL Claimable for Employers Registered with HRDF</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="84" src="media/wysiwyg/14054931_1763340620617768_4715474791535353517_n.jpg" title="HRDF claimable" width="64" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136111;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>The Certified Information Systems Security Professional (CISSP) course is a perfect companion to preparing for the CISSP Exam. It focuses specifically on the objectives for the CISSP exam introduces by (ISC)2 in May 2021. The course will review asset retention, secure provisioning, crypto attacks, machine learning tools, threat hunting, risk-based access control, zero trust, SAML, SOAR, CASB, securing microservices, containers, managed services, and many other topics, while helping you identify areas of weakness and improving your conceptual knowledge and hands-on skills.</p>\n<p>The goal of this course is to provide you with all the tools you need to prepare for the CISSP Exam &mdash; including preparation hints, test-taking tips, time-saving strategies, self-assessment questions, and practice exams &mdash; to increase your chances of passing the exam on your first try.</p>\n<p><strong>Duration:</strong>&nbsp;5 days of training</p>\n<p><strong>Audience:</strong></p>\n<p>IT security professionals and security leaders who are interested in seeking certification or who need to maintain their certification.</p>\n<p><strong>Prerequisites:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>1-2 years professional experience with IT security</li>\n<li>Experience working with IT security</li>\n<li>Fluency in security procedures such as business continuity planning, disaster planning, and risk assessment</li>\n</ul class="bullet">\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="http://www.hrdf.com.my/wps/portal/PSMB/MainEN/Schemes/HRDF/" title="HRDF claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRDF SBL Claimable for Employers Registered with HRDF</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="84" src="media/wysiwyg/14054931_1763340620617768_4715474791535353517_n.jpg" title="HRDF claimable" width="64" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136116;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Blockchain is essentially a decentralised and distributed database peer-to-peer technology (Web3) that was popularised by the Bitcoin global cryptocurrency platform since 2009. There has been a lot of hype around Blockchain and Web3 technology in recent times. Almost all Fin-Tech heavy weights are pouring investments into various Blockchain projects such as DeFi, GameFi, Metaverse, NFT etc .Governments and regulators are also equally interested in this disruptive technology.</p>\n\n<p>The potential applications for Blockchains and Bitcoin-like cryptocurrencies are enormous.&nbsp;This course will teach you the fundamentals on Crypto,, NFT, Metaverse, DeFi, GameFi. It also covers the Crypto Security and how you can protect your Crypto from hacking and fraud.</p>\n\n\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp SBL KHAS Claimable for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>\n' WHERE value_id=136170;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Algorithmic trading relies on computer programs that execute algorithms to automate some or all elements of a trading strategy. Algorithms are a sequence of steps or rules designed to achieve a goal. They can take many forms and facilitate optimization throughout the investment process, from idea generation to asset allocation, trade execution, and risk management.</p>\n<p>Machine learning (ML) and Deep Learning (DL) involves algorithms that learn rules or patterns from data to achieve a goal such as minimizing a prediction error.&nbsp;&nbsp;ML and DL algorithms can extract information from data to support or automate key investment activities. This course will teach the basis of ML and DL used for trading.</p>\n\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp SBL KHAS Claimable for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>\n\n' WHERE value_id=136222;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Elevate your understanding of Robotic Process Automation with our UIPath RPA Essential Training. This meticulously crafted course provides a deep dive into core UIPath operations, offering participants a robust foundation in Control Flow Scripting, and a comprehensive grasp of automating emails, web interactions, and file operations.</p>\n<p>Beyond the basics, the training delves into sophisticated realms of RPA, including proficient error handling techniques, leveraging the UIPath Orchestrator for centralized robot management, and exploring the potential of cognitive activities. Whether you are a novice or a professional seeking to upgrade your RPA skills, this course provides the expertise you need.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136228;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Robotic process automation (RPA) is revolutionizing business processes everywhere. Automation Anywhere is enterprise-grade RPA software that puts automation in the hands of your workers—without sacrificing reliability or security. This course introduces learners to the potential for automating repetitive tasks using Automation Anywhere. Review the components of Automation Anywhere architecture, and then discover how to create a bot step by step. You can study the three case studies included with the course to better understand how the automation process can be customized for your business.</p>\n\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>\n\n' WHERE value_id=136239;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Unlock the power of data-driven narratives with our Data Storytelling with Tableau course. This program commences by focusing on the essentials: designing compelling storyboards that lay the groundwork for effective data communication. Our expert-guided training ensures that participants not only understand but also skillfully apply various storytelling techniques to make their data speak volumes.</p>\n<p>Beyond mere theory, the course accentuates on knowing your audience and crafting visual narratives that resonate. By integrating effective visuals, participants will learn to convey complex data points with clarity and impact. The program culminates with practical sessions, enabling attendees to distill complex datasets into clear, compelling, and actionable stories. Whether you''re presenting to stakeholders or aiming to influence business decisions, mastering data storytelling with Tableau arms you with the tools to do it persuasively.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136248;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a journey to mastery with our Advanced RPA Training focused on UIPath. This course, curated for professionals and enthusiasts alike, delves into intricate aspects of RPA including data scraping, orchestrator operations, and more, ensuring a comprehensive grasp on the subject.</p>\n<p>Our curriculum accentuates on the key highlights: from efficient data scraping and recording methods to the seamless integration of UIPath Orchestrator. Further, participants will understand the nuances of error handling and the fascinating realm of cognitive activities. By the conclusion, attendees will possess a robust set of skills, poised to lead in the evolving landscape of Robotic Process Automation.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136379;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a transformative journey with the Qlik Sense Business Analytics Training at Tertiary Courses. Qlik Sense, a front-runner in the business analytics sphere, offers a dynamic platform for data-driven decision-making. This course has been meticulously designed to ensure participants grasp the nuances of the tool, enabling them to extract actionable insights from their data.</p>\n<p>Commencing with an in-depth look at the Qlik Sense Interface, trainees will be adeptly guided on connecting to diverse data sources, ensuring a robust foundation. From there, the course delves into the intricacies of data modelling, preparation, and creating compelling visualizations. By mastering Qlik Sense expressions and the potent set analysis feature, participants will be equipped to transform raw data into visual stories, making strategic decisions with precision. Join us and harness the power of Qlik Sense for superior business analytics.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136386;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Immerse yourself in the field of Sustainability Reporting with a focus on GRI (Global Reporting Initiative) standards through our comprehensive course. Gain the essential knowledge and skills needed to produce high-quality sustainability reports adhering to globally recognized standards. Understand how to assess, measure, and effectively communicate your organization''s impact on critical sustainability issues such as climate change, human rights, governance, and social well-being.</p>\n<p>Our course provides a deep dive into the GRI standards, equipping you with the know-how to contribute to your company''s sustainability agenda and increase its corporate responsibility profile. This knowledge will empower you to drive sustainable development within your organization, paving the way for enhanced business performance and a better future for all. Align your business goals with the larger objective of sustainability and make a lasting impact on your organization and society at large</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136400;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Step into the realm of cutting-edge Business Intelligence with our QlikView Business Intelligence Training course. QlikView, a leading BI tool, empowers businesses to transform raw data into actionable insights, and this training offers a holistic approach to mastering its vast capabilities.</p>\n<p>Starting with the essentials of creating dynamic data visualizations, you''ll progress to loading data effectively and building captivating interactive dashboards that offer real-time insights. Dive deeper into the heart of QlikView with intricate scripting, data modeling techniques, and learn to craft precise expressions to meet business requirements. Further enhance your BI skills with set analysis, ensuring data interpretation is both thorough and precise. Concluding with an understanding of QlikView''s robust security protocols, you''ll leave with the confidence and knowledge to utilize QlikView in driving data-led business decisions.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136429;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Step into the next level of accounting proficiency with our Advanced QuickBooks Online Plus Training. Designed for those aiming for mastery, this course delves deep into the complexities of budgeting, streamlining payroll processes, and managing projects seamlessly within QuickBooks. Get insights into bank reconciliation and learn the intricacies of handling fixed assets and their depreciation.</p>\n<p>The course doesn&rsquo;t just stop at traditional features. Embrace the modern era of accounting by exploring the full potential of QuickBooks Mobile Apps, ensuring you can manage your finances on-the-go. Whether you''re an experienced accountant or an entrepreneur seeking to expand your financial expertise, this training promises a thorough understanding and hands-on practice. Join Tertiary Courses to unlock superior accounting capabilities.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136464;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Dive into the revolutionary world of Robotic Process Automation with our Basic Robotic Process Automation course using UIPath. This course is designed for individuals aiming to harness the power of automation, providing foundational knowledge on UIPath operations &ndash; a leading tool in the RPA industry.</p>\n<p>Delve deeper into the course highlights that focus on UIPath Operations, offering a comprehensive understanding of control flow scripting. By the end of this course, participants will be equipped with practical skills, laying a solid foundation for advanced automation projects and tasks.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136466;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<h2><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">This course is currently not available</span></strong></h2>\n<p>ITIL V3 Foundations Boot Camp is a 2-day intensive program by an experienced professional&nbsp;who has an actual experience in implementing best ITIL best practices and designed to help&nbsp;participants achieve ITIL Foundation certification</p>\n<h2>Why ITIL?</h2>\n<p>IT organizations are faced with a rapidly evolving where standardization on procedures is&nbsp;becoming a major requirement and a critical success factor. Information Technology&nbsp;Infrastructure Library (ITIL), is the preeminent framework for managing IT service delivery&nbsp;around the world. ITIL defines a service lifecycle model that prescribes specific processes&nbsp;and activities during the design, development, delivery and support of IT services.&nbsp;ITIL&rsquo;s body of knowledge represent the consensus derived from over a decade of work and&nbsp;experience by thousands of IT professionals world-wide, earning for it the status as de facto&nbsp;world standard for IT best practices. More and more organizations are therefore mandating&nbsp;ITIL certification for their staff and contractors.</p>\n<h2>Benefits</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Career growth for potential salary increase and/or promotion</li>\n<li>Complete &ldquo;turnkey&rdquo; comprehensive ITIL V3 training program to help gain ITIL&nbsp;foundation certification</li>\n<li>Gain practical ITIL skills you will immediately use on the job</li>\n<li>Increase your effectiveness on the job in days</li>\n<li>Actionable learning, case studies, classroom discussions and Q&amp;A sessions</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Who Should Attend</h2>\n<p><br />ITIL V3 Foundations boot camp is an introductory-level course intended for IT professionals&nbsp;responsible for developing, supporting, and operating application-based IT services (e.g.,&nbsp;messaging) and infrastructure-based IT services (e.g., network services).</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<p>At the end of the course, participants will sit for the ITIL Foundation exam in Singapore . Those who pass scoring at least 65% will be awarded ITIL Foundation Certificate from AXELOS and the test will be conducted through PEOPLECERT..</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n</div>\n' WHERE value_id=136524;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a transformative journey into the revolutionary world of blockchain and Bitcoin with our introductory course. Participants will unravel the intricate fabric of blockchain technology, gaining a thorough understanding of its myriad real-world applications. The module delves deep into the phenomenon of cryptocurrency, illuminating the mechanics behind Bitcoin and the intricacies of Bitcoin mining.</p>\n<p>Further elevating the learning experience, attendees will venture into the groundbreaking realm of Tokenomics and the captivating world of Non-Fungible Tokens (NFTs). By the culmination of this course, participants will possess a solid foundational knowledge, enabling them to navigate the ever-evolving blockchain landscape with confidence. With Tertiary Courses, step confidently into the future of decentralized digital assets and technology.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136615;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Step into the captivating world of 3D modeling with Rhino, one of the leading tools in the design industry, and unravel its potential with our structured training at Tertiary Courses. This immersive course dives deep into the essence of why Rhino is a preferred choice among designers, guiding participants through the nuances of viewport navigation, object manipulation using commands, and the intricate process of creating curves, surfaces, and solids. Each lesson is designed to empower learners with a blend of theoretical insights and hands-on experience, ensuring a holistic grasp of the software.</p>\n<p>From executing basic transformations to molding solids using primitives and extruding curves, participants will traverse a meticulously curated curriculum that leaves no stone unturned. The course elucidates essential techniques such as snapping to objects and planes, and mastering operations like trimming, splitting, rotating, and copying to achieve precision in designs. Furthermore, our module on Rhino Architecture Design offers a deep dive into architectural modeling, paving the way for participants to harness the full power of Rhino in their projects.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136681;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>This course is designed to teach beginners the fundamentals of Adobe Lightroom, a powerful photo editing software that enables photographers to organize, edit, and share their images efficiently. Students will learn the basic interface and tools of Lightroom, as well as how to import, organize and manage their photos.</p>\n<p>The course will also cover the fundamental editing tools such as exposure, contrast, color balance, sharpening and noise reduction, as well as advanced techniques such as local adjustments and retouching. Students will learn how to apply these tools to improve their images, create their own presets and synchronize their edits across multiple images.</p>\n\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>\n' WHERE value_id=136689;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Unlock the potential of your data with our Data Visualisation with Tableau course at Tertiary Courses. Tableau, recognized globally for its intuitive design and visualization prowess, is a fundamental tool for anyone looking to present data in an impactful manner. This course is meticulously designed to empower participants with the knowledge and techniques to harness the full capabilities of Tableau, ensuring data is not just seen but understood.</p>\n<p>Starting with the basics, participants will learn the art of seamlessly connecting to varied data sources and joining related datasets. As the training progresses, attendees will dive into creating rich visualizations, implementing custom calculations, and mastering the intricacies of crosstabs and pivoting. The course also sheds light on advanced topics like data merging and effective data highlighting. By the end, you''ll be equipped to weave compelling data narratives using Tableau, turning raw numbers into captivating visuals.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136832;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Embark on a comprehensive journey into the world of QuickBooks Pro with our Accounting Essential Training. This course meticulously covers the setup of a new company file, managing the chart of accounts, integrating bank accounts and credit cards, setting up sales tax, and creating detailed profiles for customers, vendors, and employees. Additionally, participants will gain hands-on experience in generating estimates, purchase orders, and invoices while understanding the nitty-gritty of receiving payments and online banking with QuickBooks.</p>\n<p>As an added advantage, the course delves into the techniques of sharing QuickBooks efficiently with other stakeholders. We also ensure participants become proficient in handling refunds, credits, and employee payments. By the end of this training, you''ll be well-equipped to run insightful reports and optimize your financial operations using QuickBooks Pro. Elevate your accounting proficiency with Tertiary Courses.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136877;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>Unlock the potential of 3D design with our SketchUp Essential Training at Tertiary Courses. This comprehensive course is designed to immerse participants into the world of SketchUp, providing hands-on experience and understanding of its powerful features. Begin by learning to craft precise camera views, shade faces and edges, and manipulate objects through selection, movement, scaling, and rotation. Explore foundational drawing techniques, from creating circles and polygons to adding depth with 3D text, and enhance your sketches with detailed labeling.</p>\n<p>Our tailored curriculum further delves into the essentials of working with layers, integrating components from the 3D Warehouse, and the art of applying materials to breathe life into your designs. Mapping textures effectively and understanding the nuances of exporting sketches in both 2D and 3D formats will ensure participants leave equipped with a well-rounded set of skills. Whether you''re an aspiring designer or a seasoned professional, this course will refine your abilities, setting you on the path to SketchUp mastery.</p>\n<h2>Certificate</h2>\n<p>All participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Courses after achieved at least 75% attendance.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>' WHERE value_id=136921;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>The Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) course offers an in-depth dive into the world of networking, providing participants with the knowledge and skills needed to design, configure, and manage both wired and wireless network connections. Whether you''re new to the field or looking to enhance your professional portfolio, this course ensures a solid grounding in core networking concepts, aligning with industry best practices and standards.</p>\n<p>Beyond just theoretical understanding, our CCNA training emphasizes hands-on experience and real-world application. Participants will tackle a range of networking challenges, from IP addressing and routing to network security and automation, all under the guidance of experienced instructors with deep industry insights. By the end of the course, you''ll be well-prepared to ace the CCNA certification exam and set a strong foundation for a thriving career in networking.</p>\n<h2>Learning Outcomes</h2>\n<p>By end of the course, learners should be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>LO1: Identify key network components for Cisco network and translate organisational needs to technical requirements.</li>\n<li>LO2:&nbsp;Implement servers and devices following the organisation&rsquo;s network plan and manage Cisco network as per guidelines.</li>\n<li>LO3:&nbsp;Identify appropriate Cisco network management tools to implement regular network reporting and stability assessment procedures.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Course Brochure</h2>\n<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/11MnBn78-sAQBYJCsFBEDS8q8m2x1iV_e/view?usp=sharing" title="WSQ - Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) Brochure" target="_blank">Download WSQ - Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) Brochure</a></span></p>\n<h2>Skills Framework</h2>\n<p>This course follows the guideline of&nbsp;<strong><span lang="EN">Network Configuration </span><span lang="EN">ICT-DIT-3009-1.1&nbsp;</span></strong><span></span><strong>&nbsp;</strong>under ICT Skills Framework</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong> - Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>OpenCerts from SkillsFuture Singapor</strong>e - After passing the assessment(s) and achieving at least 75% attendance, participants will receive a OpenCert (aka Statement of Achievement) from SkillsFuture Singapore, certifying that they have achieved the Competency Standard(s) in the above Skills Framework.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Certification</strong> -&nbsp;The participant will be able to attempt the 200-301 Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) certification exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) accreditation from CISCO. This certification validates a participant''s proficiency in configuring, operating, and troubleshooting medium-sized networks.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://home.pearsonvue.com/cisco.aspx" title="Cisco Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>. We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center. Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n<div style=" width: 100%; padding: 10px; border-radius: 25px;">\n<h2>WSQ Funding</h2>\n<p>WSQ funding is only applicable to Singaporeans and PR. Subject to eligibility, the funding support is subjected to funding caps.</p>\n<table border="1" style="width: 100%;">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan="5" style="text-align: center;"><strong></strong><strong></strong><strong><span>Effective for courses starting from 1 Jan 2024</span></strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Full Fee</strong></td>\n<td rowspan="2" style="text-align: center;"><strong>GST</strong></td>\n<td colspan="3" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Nett Fee after Funding (Incl. GST)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><span><strong>Baseline</strong></span></td>\n<td style="text-align: center;"><strong>MCES / SME</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$2500</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$225.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$1,475.00</td>\n<td style="text-align: center;">$975.00</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Baseline: Singaporean/PR age 21 and above<br />MCES(Mid-Career Enhanced Subsidy): S''porean age 40 &amp; above</p>\n<p>Upon registration, we will advise further on how to tap on the WSQ Training Subsidy.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can pay the nett fee (a<span>fter the WSQ training subsidy)&nbsp;</span>by the following :</p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit (SFEC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore-registered companies can tap on $10000 SFEC to cover out-of-pocket expenses.<a href="https://skillsfuture.gobusiness.gov.sg/course-directory/courses/TGS-2023037854" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit SkillsFuture Enterprise Credit</span></a></p>\n<h3>SkillsFuture Credit (SFC)</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their SFC to offset course fee payable after funding but the $4,000 Additional SFC (Mid-Career Support) cannot be used. <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023037854" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here for SkillsFuture Credit submission</span></a></p>\n<h3>UTAP</h3>\n<p>Eligible NTUC members can apply for 50% of the unfunded fee from UTAP, capped up to $250/year and for members aged 40 and above, capped up to $500/year. <a href="https://www.ntuc.org.sg/wps/portal/up2/home/eserviceslanding?id=6bc1ca2c-ce81-4acb-a28f-c0be586e185f" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Click here to submit UTAP</span></a></p>\n<h3>PSEA</h3>\n<p>Eligible Singapore Citizens can use their PSEA funds to offset course fee payable after funding.</p>\nTo check for Post-Secondary Education Account (PSEA) eligibility for this course, <a href="https://www.myskillsfuture.gov.sg/content/portal/en/training-exchange/course-directory/course-detail.html?courseReferenceNumber=TGS-2023037854" title="SkillsFuture Credit" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000; text-decoration-line: underline;">Visit SkillsFuture (course code: TGS-2023037854) </span></a>\n<ul>\n<li>Scroll down to &ldquo;Keyword Tags&rdquo; to verify for PSEA eligibility.</li>\n<li>If there is &ldquo;PSEA&rdquo; under keyword tags, the course is eligible for PSEA.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Once you are eligible for PSEA, please download and fill up the <span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://www.moe.gov.sg/-/media/files/financial-matters/psea-ad-hoc-withdrawal-form.pdf" title="PSEA Withdrawal Form" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline; color: #ff0000;">PSEA Withdrawal Form</span></a></span> and email to us.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>' WHERE value_id=138376;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<p>In the ever-evolving landscape of networking, the Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) stands as a hallmark of foundational proficiency. Our CCNA Exam Preparation course is tailored to ensure that aspiring network professionals grasp the intricate details of networking, setting them on the path to certification success. We demystify the complexities of networking, making it accessible and understandable for all.</p>\n<p>From routing and switching to network security and automation, our course encompasses every domain of the CCNA syllabus. With a blend of theoretical concepts and hands-on labs, learners will gain practical experience, ensuring they''re well-equipped to tackle real-world challenges post-certification. Whether you''re kickstarting your networking career or aiming to solidify your foundational knowledge, our CCNA Exam Prep is your trusted companion on this journey.</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech</strong>&nbsp;- Upon meeting at least 75% attendance and passing the assessment(s), participants will receive a Certificate of Completion from Tertiary Infotech.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>External Certification</strong>&nbsp;-&nbsp;The participant will be able to attempt the 200-301 Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) certification exam after attending this course. Upon passing the exam, you will receive the Cisco Certified Network Associate (CCNA) accreditation from CISCO. This certification validates a participant''s proficiency in configuring, operating, and troubleshooting medium-sized networks.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Certification Exam at Pearson Vue</h2>\n<p>Once you are prepared for the exam, you can register for the certification&nbsp;<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="https://home.pearsonvue.com/cisco.aspx" title="Cisco Certification" target="_blank">here</a></span>. We are Authorised Pearson Vue Testing Center. You can take the certification exam at our test center.&nbsp;Note that the course fee does not include the certification exam fee.</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant</h2>\n<p><span style="font-size: medium; color: #ff0000;"><a href="https://hrdcorp.gov.my/employer-guidelines/" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" target="_blank"><span style="color: #ff0000;">HRD Corp Claimable Course for Employers Registered with HRD Corp</span></a></span></p>\n<p><img alt="HRDF claimable" height="100" src="media/wysiwyg/Logo_HRD_Corp_Claimable_programme-1.jpg" title="HRDF claimable-HRD Corp claimable" width="100" /></p>' WHERE value_id=139683;
UPDATE catalog_product_entity_text SET value='<h2><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">This course is currently not available</span></strong></h2>\n<p>ITIL V3 Foundations Boot Camp is a 2-day intensive program by an experienced professional&nbsp;who has an actual experience in implementing best ITIL best practices and designed to help&nbsp;participants achieve ITIL Foundation certification</p>\n<h2>Why ITIL?</h2>\n<p>IT organizations are faced with a rapidly evolving where standardization on procedures is&nbsp;becoming a major requirement and a critical success factor. Information Technology&nbsp;Infrastructure Library (ITIL), is the preeminent framework for managing IT service delivery&nbsp;around the world. ITIL defines a service lifecycle model that prescribes specific processes&nbsp;and activities during the design, development, delivery and support of IT services.&nbsp;ITIL&rsquo;s body of knowledge represent the consensus derived from over a decade of work and&nbsp;experience by thousands of IT professionals world-wide, earning for it the status as de facto&nbsp;world standard for IT best practices. More and more organizations are therefore mandating&nbsp;ITIL certification for their staff and contractors.</p>\n<h2>Benefits</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Career growth for potential salary increase and/or promotion</li>\n<li>Complete &ldquo;turnkey&rdquo; comprehensive ITIL V3 training program to help gain ITIL&nbsp;foundation certification</li>\n<li>Gain practical ITIL skills you will immediately use on the job</li>\n<li>Increase your effectiveness on the job in days</li>\n<li>Actionable learning, case studies, classroom discussions and Q&amp;A sessions</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Who Should Attend</h2>\n<p><br />ITIL V3 Foundations boot camp is an introductory-level course intended for IT professionals&nbsp;responsible for developing, supporting, and operating application-based IT services (e.g.,&nbsp;messaging) and infrastructure-based IT services (e.g., network services).</p>\n<h2>Certification</h2>\n<p>At the end of the course, participants will sit for the ITIL Foundation exam in Singapore . Those who pass scoring at least 65% will be awarded ITIL Foundation Certificate from AXELOS and the test will be conducted through PEOPLECERT..</p>\n<h2>Funding and Grant Applications</h2>\n<p>No funding is available for this course</p>\n</div>\n' WHERE value_id=140780;
